text: This is absolutely one of the worst McDonald's there is an Metairie . I used to come here five days a week and out of those five days four days would be something wrong or incorrect with my food. On my way to work I decided to OK well let me try it again I have been in line and drive-through for 21 minutes finally asking the drive-through cashier what's going on she claims there's only four employees working. They just spent thousands and thousands of dollars remodeling this McDonald's why when the doors need to be shut . And if anyone from McDonald's thinks I'm exaggerating do me a favor take a ride through the drive-through I can promise you something will be wrong . I am not kidding at all they just handed me my food and it was the wrong order. I swear I cannot even get over this store it's just too unbelievable to even believe

name: KFC
categories: Restaurants, Fast Food, Chicken Wings, Chicken Shop
text:
If I owned this business, I would be firing everyone that works there, including my manager.  First and foremost, every time I go there, they are out of something!!  EVERY TIME!!!  You are a chicken joint, for you to NOT have any chicken product you sell on a regular basis is an absolute joke.  

This might have something to do with the fact that, although the restaurant closes at 10pm, the employees are ready to go with chairs up and sign off at 8pm.  Either you are too lazy to fire the deep frier up, since you shut it down two hours early, or whoever does your ordering is incompetent.  Needless to say, I live a mile from you, but I drive six miles to the next closest KFC just to avoid the bad news that you don't have whatever I order available, consistently.

text:
It appears that this KFC suffers from extremely poor management. In March we went on a 40 degree day and they had the inside temp no higher than 45 to 50. Three weeks ago there was a horrible stench pervading the restaurant, but today the employees decided to skip the subtle ways to drive people away and simply locked the doors early. text: I wish I could give a zero...they are the worse Wendy's I have ever been to. they take forever with your food and they still get your order wrong. Their food is nasty, under or overcooked and prepared sloppy. And they have no customer service skills what so ever they are rude and argumentative. I ordered at the drive thru today I asked for a chicken pub meal with baconator fries, large. The lady puts it in as a burger I say I'm sorry (I apologized even though she was wrong) I asked for chicken. She huffs and puffs in the microphone then gives me my total. I get my food and processed to pull off and realize they did not give the bacanator fries. So I turned around and bring this to the girl at the Windows attention. Her response was not I'm sorry I apologize or coming right up she tells me, you specifically voided the baconator fries. I say What! no I didn't (I'm confused because I know what I said). she says yes you did it says it right her. I say how are you going to tell me what I said when you didn't even take the order? She says, you got what you paid for! now, while she was arguing with me about what I asked for, the women who actually took my order was making the baconator fries. Because she knows she made the error not me. Instead of her speaking up about her wrong doing or someone telling this girl she is not getting paid to argue with the customer she is getting paid for CUSTOMER SERVICE no said or did anything. I was so discussed by how I was treated I WILL NEVER ORDER FROM THERE AGAIN!

text: Very clean, ordered at self serve kiosk all was well, completed my order, and it began no number tents at kiosk, ok confused young lady at the front counter came out and determined I didn't need one since I was the only customer. I as I waited to pay (about 4 min) I did notice a lot of activity in the back apparently drive thru was swamped I assumed, finally the same confused young lady returned to the counter. My bill was $11.?? Gave her 2 - 5's & 2 - 1's the poor thing I've seen deer less scared. She counted it at least 3 times and finally entered it in the register and with a little disbelieve saw I actually got change. Ok thank God, I asked for my cup and got my soda from the fountain, 15 minutes later I got my self another, 5 minutes later I got my food and it was good and hot but not fast. Upon leaving I did notice that the drive thru line was busy maybe that's the reason who knows?

categories: Restaurants, Fast Food, Chicken Wings, Chicken Shop
text:
Since there is a limited amount of KFCs, do to locations closing permanently, I made my way all the way down from the SW side of town to Golflinks/Kolb for family meal. 

As expected the line was long (it is the weekend after all) and we waited. The the drive thru cashier (Keyla) was cutting us off as the ordered with an extremely annoyed and bothered tone. She rushed us and as we approached the window, she was still giving a negative and rude attitude. She handed the food upset after we asked her for a receipt. 

I'm not one to complain when I see tired and exhausted ppl attending me at a fast food restaurant. However, I was very I pleased with the customer service delivered. I will not be returning and I hope this fast food "professional" receives some type of discipline and training. 

All I hope is that their word stays true to what they state their commitment is: 
"We are committed to using our voice to speak up but more importantly, using this time to LISTEN, LEARN, and act to CREATE POSITIVE SOCIAL CHANGE. We have to do more. We will do more."

name: KFC
categories: Chicken Wings, Fast Food, American (Traditional), Restaurants, Chicken Shop
text: What in the world happened to KFC? I moved away from Edmonton years ago, back in town to visit family, stopped in for lunch, and ordered a combo that came with a variety of popcorn chicken, tenders, original recipe chicken, fries and slaw. Original chicken was soggy, lukewarm, and extremely greasy and fatty. Tenders were a very strange soft texture, nothing like fresh chicken I've eating anywhere else, A major burger chains chicken nuggets are 10x better than the popcorn chicken, which is inexcusable for a restaurant with Chicken in its name. Fries were soggy and not fresh. (And yes I are in the restaurant) nothing was fresh, the coleslaw was by far the best thing about this meal. One restroom was out of order and the other had not a drop of soap left, meaning the staff isn't even washing their hands properly before working. Inexcusable even for a fast food restaurant, no wonder there were no other people here during the middle of lunch. I will not be returning to kfc, probably ever.

name: Pizza Hut
categories: Chicken Wings, Italian, Fast Food, Pizza, Restaurants
text:
Absolutely unacceptable experience. 

I have ordered from here several times for both delivery and pickup. Last week, we ordered with a 35 minute estimate, and after 1 hour and 20 minutes called the restaurant to ask about our pizza. We were hung up on twice, and finally put on hold for 5 minutes only to be told that our order hadn't left the building. The person on the phone was incredibly short and rude about it, and hung up on me when I told her to cancel the order.

Then, I received a call from "customer service" to confirm my cancellation. When I tried to talk about the issue, I was rudely cut off and the caller rattled off the "discount-time policy" to me. Essentially, I was told to sit and wait for my pizza (it was 11pm at this time) and whenever it came I would get a $ discount based on the amount of time after the window. So, essentially, wait more than two hours for pizza, receive no call that it will be late, and screw off. 

This really wasn't even about the discount at this point, it was ultimately about how rude and unpleasant everyone was being.

I emailed the company the next day. Received a can email "will contact you in 3 business days." Guess what didn't happen? Emailed back, received a canned "escalation" email for another three business days. In 19 minutes that window is up, haha.

I don't expect much from chain pizza, but Pizza Hut couldn't even meet the ABSOLUTE minimum.

name: Wendy's
categories: Restaurants, Fast Food, Burgers
text:
Literally writing this review as I stand in line. This place is absolutely pathetic. I waited in the drive thru for 9 minutes, YES 9 minutes with no acknowledgement and there was a car/customer ahead of me, he had the same issue. I'm not even going to get into the fact that there were 3 cars behind me with customers who left. So, I decided to go inside to see what the problem might be. There is a line 10 people long and the employees are literally operating on turtle speed. There is no sense of urgency or even a concern of care for the customers. One has a headset on, but I have yet to see him take an order at the drive thru. 

I never visit Wendy's bc I try to stay away from most fast food places, but I had a taste for nuggets today. I can honestly say I will NEVER step foot in this establishment again or stop by for ANYTHING! This place should be shut down for customer service reasons alone!! Your workers simply don't care and I assume corporate doesn't care either!! 

By the way, Chik Fil A is about 2 miles away, I bet I will see some old Wendy's customers there.

name: Adventure Alley
categories: Active Life, Bowling, Go Karts, Arcades, Restaurants, Pizza, Arts & Entertainment
text:
I decided to check this place out, against the reviews I read. I like to make my own judgement of an establishment.
Being a Saturday & home with two kids, I said, "heck it, let's go!"
Upon arriving, the parking lot was almost empty. I was like "yuusss", it's not packed.
I bought myself & kids the wristbands that allowed us to enjoy certain things unlimited times for 3 hours. The price for those? $105.
Come to find out, my almost 4 year old was unable to ride the go karts & my 8 year old was unable to drive one, unless he was riding with me. We were unable to enjoy that, seeing how I couldn't just leave my 4 year old on the sideline, unattended.
The mini golf was pretty cool, but unattended. I had a teen getting in the way while I was trying to play with my kids.
The bumper cars was another thing we were unable to do. Seeing how they had like 4 available & the others were broken down on the track. Even if they were all up & running, I didn't see a two seater one, for those of us who have small kiddos who need to ride with us. 
Half of the arcade games were not functioning.
As for the "health measurements" they claim to practice, WHERE?
I was there for 3 hours, & not once did I see someone sanitize something.
The people working there look like high schoolers who hate their job. No excitement from employees what so ever, then again, with a place like this, I'd be pretty dang depressed too & would only be there to get a paycheck.
NOT worth the drive.
NOT worth your time.
NOT worth your money.
Now that I've experienced this place myself, I will not be returning.

name: Domino's Pizza
categories: Pizza, Chicken Wings, Restaurants, Sandwiches
text:
I'm not sure what lead to the mostly-negative reviews that come before this one, but I have been to this establishment about three times, all with positive results. I have opted for takeout each time, and speed, service, and price have all been stellar. For eight bucks ($8.50 w/tax), you can get a large pizza with three toppings. 
I haven't experience any delays, attitude issues (staff is friendly, in fact), or anything out of the ordinary. Again, I've got no idea why there are so many 1 stars on here. Maybe this was before a lot of staff turnover, but I have had nothing but smooth sailing with this store.

(I took a star off because those "specialty chicken" dishes are a little lacking)

name: Jack in the Box
categories: Mexican, Tacos, Restaurants, Breakfast & Brunch, Fast Food, Burgers
text:
This Jack in the box used to be good when it first opened about a year ago.   Unfortunately, it is terrible now.  I went here often but will not go again.  They do not care about the quality of food they put out.  Their eggs and hash browns obviously sit out forever.  The eggs on the sandwich are cold and rubbery. The hash browns are always cold greasy and soggy.  It's the same with their fries. Always cold and taste old. I would be embarrassed if I was the manager putting food out like that.  Manager needs to address the quality of the midnight shift food in a major way.  I literally had to throw my food away and go get something else up the road.  

When you give a company your money, you should expect to get what they advertise.

name: Pizza Hut
categories: Chicken Wings, Restaurants, Fast Food, Pizza, Italian
text: We put in an order around 5:50 pm for delivery for 7:15 pm as that is when we would be home from picking up my stepdaughter. My husband who placed the order got a text around 6:15 pm that our order was out for delivery. We only live around 10 minutes from the store meaning it would be delivered almost an hour early. We got home and picked our food up off the cement floor of the porch rather than the railing and being it inside. The bottom box of pizza had ants all over it which when set on the counter before we realized it, got the ants all over the counter and when opening the box to check out the pizza there were ants in the box as well. We had to throw the whole pizza out. My husband called the store to make a complaint (not for free food or anything but just to make it known) and the lady who answered the phone replied with the time is not guaranteed. When asked then why is it an option she responded well you chose contactless delivery, which is true, but what does that have to do with time and what would have happened had we chose contact? What would have been the protocol then? My husband asked to speak to a manager was put on hold for 30 minutes so he tried calling from my phone, the same woman immediately answered and my husband asked to speak to a manager, the lady out him on hold on my phone and hung up on him in his phone. So my husband drove to the store. As soon as he walked in he again made it known he was not asking for free food or anything of the sort but simply looking for answers and only drove there after being treated poorly by the lady who answered the phone twice. The manager at the store basically brushed him off and said the same thing the employee did. Which none of it makes sense. Don't offer a time if it won't be honored and contactless delivery or not has nothing to do with the time of delivery. This store has horrible customer service and lost a customer, not that it matters to a big corporation anyway.

name: McDonald's
categories: Restaurants, Coffee & Tea, Burgers, Fast Food, Food
text:
I live a few miles from this site and it is not in the best neighborhood. I go through it any time I have business at the county offices. It really is the area you don't want to linger in unless you've got some sort of Charles Bronson life quest going.

And it's not fair to blame the rank and file behind the counter for a cheap paint job or the quality of a bathroom shared with a gas station.

That having been said this is a place to avoid. it has now made news for an employee beating a customer unconscious with the TV news showing him brutally kicking the man when he's down. 

and even that I can't site the other employees for it, though let's be honest that alone is enough to avoid this place. where the real problem comes in is how the staff responded. Local TV news crews were just told to get out and it was 'private property' when they went to the employee's last known address a foul mouthed woman, IN McDONALD's UNIFORM greeted them (ha!) at the door and said, with several expletives, if they told you to get out at the McDonald's why do you think we're going to talk to you. It was clear the McDonald's had called the house to warn them. So in uniform and swearing and clearly the go to is COVER UP. 

At that point you can hold them accountable. this isn't a case of "I can't believe I work in a place where someone did this" so much as it is complicit in the act by not being up front and swearing while in uniform without a disclaimer or any statement, from management shows how this place is run.

Cleanliness, and food quality have been cited often enough in these reviews and the fact that homeless panhandlers are not stopped from harassing customers but when it reaches the point of not only criminal assault but a culture of 'cover up' instead of even a normal  corporate blank statement of we do not endorse..' or 'our customers are our greatest concern...' then clearly this is a place corporate management should take steps to removed form their books.

I don't know why these people are so miserable to try and make everyone else's days so miserable but damn go get a diff job if you don't like where you work. Screw this location for real.

categories: Coffee & Tea, Fast Food, Burgers, Food, Restaurants
text:
Went through the drive thru unfortunately & received the rudest service by a Manger that says her name is JoeAnn. She's very unprofessional speaks very unkind and her attitude is extraordinary nasty. I was told my order was NOT ready please pull up. 
This lady is a very unhinged person. She is not safe to work with the public. She's very threatening and down right rude. Back to what happened.
She wanted to fight over straws. I did not receive any with my order and once I requested them she threw a temper tantrum ran inside the building and refused to bring me any. I got out my car went inside and she wanted to debate if I received them or not. Now why would I walk inside for 2 straws if I actually had them in my bag. Apparently I have no straws. I was indeed upset at the way this person is acting. I kept calm returned to my car & came home. I could not believe my eyes that a adult woman would act like this. I mean stomping around eye rolling neck twisting yelling cursing and very unsafe behavior. 
Called back asked to speak with the manager and guess who the manager is the same temper tantrum throwing immature lady who is unsafe to be around others. I will be calling corporate I live in this community and she should not be around the general public or children. Yelling and cursing and showing aggressive behavior to others is a liability to McDonald's. Noone should have to endure her just to get a Big Mac. 
Honestly the fries were excellent today. She did not put any ice in our drink. It was hot. I won't ever return to this location long as she is employed. She's going to hurt someone.

It is worth noting that most KFC's I have tried in recent years are about the same, NOT WORTH STOPPING. My recommendation is find somewhere else to eat but not kfc. What has happened to this once iconic restaurant?

name: Jack in the Box
categories: Restaurants, Fast Food, Mexican, Tacos, Burgers, Breakfast & Brunch
text: I know this is fast food and expectations should never be high for fast food but this might possibly be the worst Jack in the Box ever. I've waited in line at the drive-thru for extended periods of time and not complained because it's the closest option available. What really pushed me over the edge though was waiting in line for 35 minutes only to find out that there was one worker handling both register and food due to a shortage of employees. All in all it took me 45 minutes to get a Munchie Meal. Now I blame myself for waiting in line and being a jackass but this has forever effected my desire to go to Jack In The Box. I decided to even give it another shot after that experience and it was shame on me. After 15 minutes of waiting on the cashier to help me, I simply asked "how much longer til we get helped?" (There was another gentleman waiting inside with me) The worker looks at me and says "if you don't want to wait you can leave." He must have helped 6 or 7 cars in the drive thru before even acknowledging there were customers inside. Mind you there was only 3 cars in the drive thru when I walked in. Never again!

name: Wendy's
categories: Hot Dogs, Burgers, Restaurants, Fast Food
text:
Gosh , I must of been lucky today!

Fellow Yelper Paul, had posted a pic of his breakfast, and there I go.

I didn't even know they had a breakfast menu.

Ordered the #4  with a coffee.

Drive they only had two cars in front of me.

I must agree the potatoes were really good.
Hot and crispy on the outside, and a lot of them. 

Chicken sandwich was perfect size for me. 

I was able to order cream for the coffee and he had added a few sugar packets!

Nice sized coffee and less mess when the cream is already added.!

Hate to say this, but this will be a go to for on the road or a quick snack breakfast!

Thanks Paul.. !

name: Pizza Hut
categories: Pizza, Restaurants, Chicken Wings, Italian, American (Traditional), Fast Food
text:
Avoid at all cost! It's not worth the hassle. Seriously, you're better off making a pizza at home. I'm convinced this store is the fifth level of hades. 


Ordered 1 pizza, cookies and a drink for delivery at 6 pm on a Tuesday. As soon as the order was placed we find out the wait time is going to be 2 hours. This wasn't really that big of a deal. The problem was the pizza arrived cold. Reasonably upset, I call to voice my concern about their pizza morals. Guy answers who is supposed to be the manager, but seriously this dude gave zero cares. He eventually offered a refund, but by the time that happened I was too hangry to care.

If you're thinking about delivery from here--just don't. 

Word of advice to Pizza Hut: if you hate delivery so much, don't offer it.

text: I have reviewed this Burger King before as horrible and have went back for another chance and it is still awful. They do not know how to make a chocolate shakes to save their life.  Also, when I asked for cheese on my whopper, they did not put it on.  I went back so that they could fix it and they still did not put cheese on it.  AND.......their double cheeseburgers are the size of a White Castle slider.  Their service is awful and the food portions are so small, it is not worth the money.  I am surprised they are still in business.

name: Steak n Shake
categories: Diners, Fast Food, Breakfast & Brunch, Desserts, Food, American (Traditional), Burgers, Restaurants
text: Although we've been hearing negative reviews since this restaurant opened I was trying to keep an open mind and assume that the restaurant is new and they are working out the kinks.  My family and I decided to eat there on December 13th around 7:00 p.m. The restaurant wasn't busy at all.  My first red flag was with the cashier that took our order.  She gave the impression that she didn't like being there.  She entered our entire order on the screen by hitting the screen really hard with her knuckles.  We sat down and waited for our order.  I noticed that the restaurant was really dirty.  There was a milk shake that spilled all over one of the tables, trash all on the floors, etc.  There were two families that came in after we did.  They got their food and we're still waiting.  I finally went up to the counter after 20 minutes had passed.  I asked one of 14 kids (we counted) behind the counter if they had an idea of how much longer it would be on our food.  The cashier yelled out that she was waiting on the chicken tenders.  As I'm going back to my table I noticed that the family that came in after we did had a little girl that was eating - yes, chicken tenders!  After we had waited a total of 25 minutes they finally called out that our food was ready.  I'm assuming by the way the kids behind the counter were treating me that they didn't appreciate me asking how much longer it would take to get our food.  These were some of the loudest, most disrespectful teenagers I had ever seen in a customer service atmosphere.  It was so obvious the way they were treating us that the manager followed us outside to ask if everything was okay.  Needless to say, this was my first and last trip there.  The manager should be embarrassed to allow his staff to 1) stand around horsing around 2) be disrespectful to their customers.  We go to the Steak and Shake in Murfreesboro frequently.  They have very nice employees there that treat the customers really well.  We've never had a bad experience there.  This is the very first negative review that I've ever written, however I felt like something needs to be done before the restaurant is forced to close down for a lack of business.

text:
I don't know why I still bother with this restaurant. I've literally had the worst service here that I've ever had at any restaurant I've ever been to. The drive thru workers ignore people...they actually ignore people. I can't express enough how awful the experience is here. I'm waiting at the speaker right now, and I've had enough time to write this review.

I didn't finish this review the first time around because I got so frustrated. I decided to give this restaurant one more go on the way to work today and they did not disappoint when it comes to being disappointing. 

I was not told that their card machine was down until I reached the end of the long line and faced the window. Being a normal person, I had no cash on me. The first woman was nice enough about it, but the next girl told me "cash only, breakfast only ! if you want to wait I guess you could, but you got to pull over" 

So here I am, pulled off to the side and once again waiting for my order. Out of spite, I will not leave without my order. The management here is clearly incompetent. I would let this go if it weren't for the rudeness of the employees. I hope someone in corporate sees this and makes a change. This location is a blemish on an otherwise well run organization.

name: Burger King
categories: Restaurants, Fast Food, Burgers
text: Visited this Burger King on 9/28/19 and it was undoubtedly the worst experience I've had at a Burger King. 2 people walked in immediately before us and approximately 6 after. There was only 1 register open which would have been fine except that the employee took over 5 minutes to take each party's order. Since each group was like 2 people, quick math says it took the folks at the back about 20 minutes to even order. I asked about ordering a promo burger that has been tv advertising, since there was nothing in the store that even showed they were carrying it. Then we waited. And waited. Like 20 minutes for 2 burgers. And then 5 more for the 3rd burger and fries. Everything was wrapped sloppily and greasy. I'm not expecting fine dining, but this was pitiful. The staff had zero urgency and generally seemed annoyed that the customers were there. I was excited to welcome this business into the area, but we won't be returning anytime soon.

name: McDonald's
categories: Fast Food, Burgers, Food, Restaurants, Coffee & Tea
text: Worst McDonalds ever. Even at 10 o'clock at night, anticipate being in line for 45 minutes as you get blocked in and skipped over by five people in the next row even though their line was empty when you got there. Also, 7 times out of 10, you will get the incorrect order in a box marked as your correct item. McDonald's has been my craving for the past eight months of my pregnancy.  I have contacted the corporate office and they were about as useful as dog crap. I also filled out a review about how that issue was handled. No feedback. I try to avoid this McDonald's at all costs, but the heart wants what the heart wants.   I've attached a photo of my Diet Coke. The lady actually looked at it and was putting a lid on it and said "Diet Coke, right?" And I said yes. And she gave me this crap. Seriously?  I'd most certainly give less than one star if possible.

name: Pizza Hut
categories: Chicken Wings, Restaurants, Fast Food, Pizza, Italian
text:
I just finished eating a pizza from this Pizza Hut and OMFG, I've never consumed so much grease before in my life! By the time I got done eating it, about 4:59 after I brought it through the front door of my house, I looked like Ne-Yo after a lusty makeout session with Russell Simmons. The late, great Pimp C would have been disgusted. Pause.

I ended up at Pizza Hut because I figured I'd have pizza, even though I just had pizza the other day (#firstworldproblems), it was getting dangerously close to Miller Time, and I wasn't emotionally equipped to try anything new, like one of these suspect places Yelp recommends that's not a chain: they could be great, or they could be one of these mom and pop joints where the pop is his own brother. I wasn't in an adventurous mood.

The good thing about gorging yourself on pizza here in end times is that you can get a pizza from pretty much anywhere for $10. Pizza Hut dropped the prices of its large pizza to $10 a couple of years ago, and everyone else followed suit, and it's been that way ever since. One time Pizza Hut try to ratchet it up to $11, or $12, depending on what you got on it, and that lasted for all of about two weeks. They must have damn near gone out of business.

I don't even sweat trying to find out what the specials are anymore. If I called one of these pizza places and they quoted me a price of more than $10, I'd just laugh in their faces and go somewhere else. Even for Meat Lovers. I think most places still do have that $28 Supreme Pizza listed on their menu, but that's just in case Kanye West calls. What does he care? He's got money to blow. His cocaine comes in a tiny glass bottle (as opposed to baggies).

Speaking of ballin' so hard, the tendency is to want to get everything you possibly can as a topping, since it's free anyway. I'm sure someone has already tried to just run down the entire list of available toppings. It's the new spending four hours at Endless Shrimp. If you're so inclined, it might even be worth trying to have them throw in something that doesn't even go on pizza, like a two liter of Coke. You know, put the entire system on trial!

I just went with pepperoni, sausage and onion, because I find that piling too many toppings on a pizza throws off the delicate balance. A true fatass would rather just eat more than one pizza. If I had it to do over again, I might just go with sausage and onion. Or sausage, onion and some other meat. Because for whatever reason, the sausage at Pizza Hut is delicious by any objective standard (they could serve it at Pi), but the pepperoni is shitty even by elementary school lunch standards.

Suddenly I'm craving a tiny carton of milk.

The pepperoni may have contributed some to the grease factor, because pepperoni pizza regardless of where you get it has that unappetizing and yet delicious layer of orange grease on top of it, but pizza from Pizza Hut also has a shedload of grease in the crust. That's how it got all over my hands. It's not like I was touching the top of it. I get a little bit messy when I'm especially enthusiastic about eating, but it's not like I turn into the developmentally disabled. #noshots

If we've learned anything at all today, it's that pizza from a national chain isn't any good, but Pizza Hut is probably the best of them all, because it's almost certainly the least healthy, and the less healthy something is the better it tastes, as a rule.

text:
I have been to this McDonald's several times and they mess my order up every time. I make my order as simple as possible for them, and they still manage to mess it up. I mean, I actually think they're trying to mess the order up at this point. 

They add things we didn't order, forget what we actually asked for, don't give us sauces or ketchup when we ask, roll their eyes if we ask for extra napkins or if we ask for any of the items that we paid for and they didn't include in our bag. 

Why do I have to ask you to put the food in my bag that I just paid for? And why do I get an attitude in response just for trying to make sure I drive off with what I purchased? 

Each time, I stay polite, and I just chalk it up as a loss. But this was the last straw. This McDonald's deserves several more 1 star votes because they're absolutely terrible.

name: Burger King
categories: Fast Food, Burgers, Restaurants
text:
We were in the area around noon and decided to grab a quick lunch. Burned out on turkey subs on honey oat, I suggested BK, because I had just seen an ad for $1.29 Whopper Jrs. We sat in the drive-thru line for around 5 minutes & didn't move, not even an inch. I (the girl on fire - - for a flame grilled burger) convinced my friends to go inside. Maybe the drive thru person was new, it had to be better inside, right?

When we got inside, there were about 10 people in line, 2 workers were taking orders, and, yeah, the line was moving, barely. Or it was until one of the 2 register workers walked away.  That's when I noticed a bunch of customers over by the drink station. They had ordered and were patiently waiting for their "fast food". One must have dared to ask a worker how much longer because the worker said loudly and with some attitude: "Four Minutes".

Finally, I got to order my $1.29 Whopper. I also ordered a small diet coke. The cashier gseemed shocked as she loudly asked me "SMALL?" I thought maybe I'm the only one left who doesn't desire extra large everything with extra mayo like the man in front of us got. After paying and while waiting a LONG time for our order, I realized my small drink set me back $1.79 plus tax. Then I saw on the "value" part of the menu that they offer a "value" sized drink for $1.00. Not sure if it's a little smaller or bigger than "small" but no way the "small" is worth 79 cents more. Really, I hope BK enjoys the extra 79 cents they got from me as much as I now cherish being a former customer.

P.S. Since we got our "fast" food and so-overpriced drink to go, I won't comment on the condition of their nasty dining area.

name: IHOP
categories: Breakfast & Brunch, Burgers, American (Traditional), Restaurants, Waffles
text:
IHOP on Valencia, Tucson. We sat in the handicap section. I called the customer service line in the 40minutes we waited for our 2 orders: senior's 2+2+2 and an entree. 
2+2+2 had a lonely piece of bacon, a piece of cool to touch sausage and scrambled eggs versus the over-medium ordered, the pancakes were cold. The entree was cold, Old/dry. No condiments, syrup, water offered. When I asked, I was given two small to-go containers with maple, none of the other typical IHOP syrups were available.
We were served After two parties with their large orders that came in after us. 
I did not ask to speak with the manager but she came over and gave me a litany of why the service and food was subpar. She also shared information that was not true. I would have given a 1 star but our waitperson was working the whole room while her partner was disappearing into the kitchen. Manager needs to review her hospitality course on how to adjust for logistic issues.

name: McDonald's
categories: Fast Food, Restaurants, Food, Burgers, Coffee & Tea
text: What prompted me to review a McDonalds rather than my normal bougie brunch joint? Well... while the food was pretty run of the mill, there were a number of minor annoyances that made my overall experience less than enjoyable. I like to dip my McChicken in buffalo sauce, but upon arriving at the first window I was told they were all out. I said that was fine and said I would like just a signature sauce, so he told me to tell them at the next window. So Strike 1 = lack of communication and lack of my favorite sauce. Then, I am given 1 sauce, which is nowhere near enough, which I do not realize until I am left with the second half of my meal and no dipping sauce. Next, as I reach into the bag, I notice that both sandwiches are almost completely visible, due to a poor wrapping job. One of the buns is halfway off of my McChicken, and that and the McGriddle are just about touching, so strike 2 = carelessness. Lastly, I am parched, so as I go for my soda, I realize they forgot to give us a straw, and I am not going to return to the "restaurant" just to retrieve a straw, so I allow my salty mouth to be dry for the remainder of my drive home, which brings me to strike 3=forgetfulness. Luckily there is never a shortage of McDonalds locations, nor is this local, so I never have to go here again and run the risk of having an unimpressed experience.

name: Wendy's
categories: Restaurants, Fast Food, Burgers
text:
I think I'm done with Wendy's. I've heard some stories that I can't stomach and today while at this location I was beyond disgusted. I was at the 2nd window and no one was wearing a mask correctly. Two of the people inside the window had their masks down around their chins and the others' masks didn't cover their noses. I asked and one of the young ladies came all out the window wondering what I was asking about. The lone gentleman fixed his mask and tried to explain to the others what I was complaining about. Another lady with no mask covering anything (I think she may have been a manager) apologized and said she was on a business call, put her mask on correctly, and excused herself to the dining room. Yes! I witnessed all of this from my car in the drive through. 

As far as the food, it wasn't even for me, it was for my kids so I don't know. What I do know....I won't be back.

categories: Restaurants, Coffee & Tea, Food, Burgers, Fast Food
text: I've been to many Mcdonalds restaurants, and I must say, this one is by far one of the worst ones. Besides the homeless people that come to the side of your window and beg for food, the employees could care less about getting your order right. Every time I order, I specifically ask for no cheese on any of my burgers and even though it is placed on the order, the cooks decide to disregard them and put cheese on it anyways. To the people who say, "who cares?", I cannot have cheese otherwise I can be extremely sick. When I get to the window, they shove your food at you and do not acknowledge you. It is clear I am not the only one who agrees when looking at other reviews. I hope this review finds itself to be useful so that more people can return in confidence.

text: I ordered two large smoothies in the drive-through Sunday July 11 (2021). They told me they had to change out the bags, that I would have to pull my car up and wait for my smoothies. I pulled up. After 20 minutes, I was still waiting, so I tried to call in on the phone to complain. But they refused to answer the phone. I went in and asked to speak to a manager. I had two African American Assistant Managers in green shirts that identified themselves as Managers. I expressed displeasure. The older of the two assistant managers got really rude with me. After green shirt African American Female got rude with me, I asked for a refund. She said she couldn't give me a refund unless I had a receipt, but I was not given a receipt. So in the absence of a receipt, I just waited for my two smoothies. I did get my two smoothies (without a receipt) after a 30 minute wait. Terrible Customer Service. I will not go to this McDonald's location again.

name: Wendy's
categories: Fast Food, Hot Dogs, Restaurants, Burgers
text:
WHY does Wendy's have the option to order online and pick up your food, if you have to wait 15 minutes in line with everyone else to pick up your order???? I ordered online, and 15 minutes later, went to pick up my food, because they don't even have "a time" you can select on the website to pick up your food. As I approached the location, there were 5 cars in front of me, so I got in line, but called the store to let them know that I was there. The manager answered, and I told her I had an online order, I was outside behind 5 cars, and asked it I pulled along side of the restaurant, if they could bring it out to me, as it was already paid for. She told me, "Nope, we can't do that...it wouldn't be fair for us to take your order before everyone else in the drive-thru". I told her again, it was a mobile order, I already placed it 15 minutes earlier, it was already paid for, and if they could bring it out to the car. She again, said "NO, you can either wait in line or you can come inside"! When I got to the window, I told the person that I had a online order, already paid for and was there to pick it up. The "Assistant Mgr." heard the anger in my voice and walked over when I asked to speak to someone in charge. Before I could say anything, she said, "Why didn't you tell us you were outside"? I told her, I called and spoke to the Mgr. and was told I had to stay in line or come in the store. She kept interrupting me as I was talking and kept saying..."Wait, Wait, Wait, give me a second" as she was trying to find my order. I asked her to get a Manager, so the Manager walked over, and I told her the same thing...why order online if it's going to take 15 minutes to sit in line with everyone else to get your food? She said you have the option to come in or to wait in line. She could not even answer the questions. They make you drive up if your order is delayed, so WHY CAN'T CUSTOMERS DRIVE UP TO THE SAME AREA TO WAIT ON THE FOOD TO BE WALKED OUT 10 STEPS TO THE WAITING CAR????
She then said, next time, hopefully we can bring it to you, and I said there will be NO NEXT TIME!!! Blows my mind how a two Managers could not even take control of a situation to walk outside to deliver a pre-paid, online order, instead of having to make a customer wait 15 minutes for the order that was placed 15 minutes prior! The food was obviously COLD when it was finally picked up and tasted horrible!

name: Subway
categories: Sandwiches, Restaurants, Fast Food
text: I hate that I even have to give this place one star.  We ordered through GrubHub... first time.  I ordered a tuna sub meal... the menu lists bacon, lettuce and tomato in the description.  The sandwish arrived with just tuna.  When my son called, he was told to bring the sandwich to the restaurant to add toppings.  What is the purpose of using and paying for the delivery service if we have to drive there to get what we ordered?  After we ate, I called to get the name of the manager and owner.  "Moe" said that he wouldn't give me the last names and wanted to know why I was asking.  I explained that he didn't make my sandwich correctly and I wanted to report him.  His English was so horrid that I couldn't even understand what he said.  Obviously he can't read or understand the description so he could make the sandwich correctly.  NEVER again will I go to Subway.. and I will post my complaint about this specific location on Facebook.

name: Wendy's
categories: Restaurants, Food, Fast Food, Burgers
text: I would have given it less than one star if I could. I had high hopes for this Wendy's when it first came to the 'hood, now I'm completely hopeless about it. Food is OK, but the SERVICE is unbearable. I don't know why I keep hoping this place will get better because I'm sadly disappointed each time. Last night, there was ONE car in front of me. I waited for in line 10 minutes before I peeled out in a hangry rage--the person ahead of me hadn't even had their order taken yet in all that time! When I went around to the drive-through window to see what the issue could have been to cause the delay -- Armed robbery in progress? Hostage situation? Someone had a medical emergency? -- I see the cashier just standing there, no other cars in sight, just staring off into space. I have never felt the need to leave a Yelp review, especially a negative one, but this place deserves it. Service is abysmal. If I feel the need for food, I'll go across the street to the Burger King which I would give a relatively better two-star review.

name: Einstein Bros. Bagels
categories: Food, Restaurants, Bagels, Sandwiches, Breakfast & Brunch
text:
After speaking to the owner of this place MR. Ferandanez he said that Dylan will not bothering me anymore. HE will be spoken too. Well that was good for at least 2 more times. When I went in there he did not give me a hard time over the Senior Rate. The following third time I went in there he started again with saying to me I am Entitled The Entitled people think who the F they are.  I reported him again to Mr. Feranandez who is the owner of this Franchise. I can not understand why a 27 yr old young man who looks like a teenager would be so terrible towards any customer. When he landed with me, He dealth with the wrong person!! 

Dylan recently wrote me a nasty email Well, I told him in response that he did not know what working hard meant. Making, preparing coffee and taking change is according to him "busting your ass" is hard work, then he never really worked on the outside world of really busting your behind.

WHEN he can open up his own store and work 18 hours a day making peanuts then let him come to me where as once owned a store and worked my behind off for less than he will ever make in his lifetime.

He is a youngman who feels that Life and Jobs owe it to him. No one owes you nothing.   I am glad that now he has quit... the other gals said he was a constant complainer, even the young gal who used to work there is also gone, she was a smoker, I can not recall her name, she was nice to me, everyone was nice to me except for this young man Dylan, who now lives in AZ... I hope that he prospers in catching a lot of fish in the fishing boats as he said to me the day before he left Einsteins. He said That everyone laughed at me. Good you have had a good laugh that I made a fool out of the person who beguilded others intergrity..

I felt that after the first 3 incidents with the 10 % that was supposed to be given to seniors was the right to get it, if you all do not want us to have it say it. No one says we got to get it I got it all from AARP who says that most resturants gives you discounts..  Then the 4th time incident happened again. I got fed up the manager about  this and He the big guy there did nothing about it and said he will talk to his young man, he did not, when I came in again and got my med coffee he was there and tried to push me around again. I got so fed up and called coporate and spoke to Mr. Ferandanz about this again. This time he said if it happens again he is fired.

Well I was glad he did not get fired he left on his own.. I guess some people need to work with the public its a hard choice to work with the public but you must to learn to respect the Customers First they pay you... you want tips which I think stinks. I buy coffee not to support your behind... let your parents do this, I raised 4 kids on this.. they never once disrespected anyone in the public working class.. and as for Us who are Entitled to this... We worked hard to come in there for Bagels and Coffee...

name: Hooters
categories: Sports Bars, American (Traditional), Restaurants, Nightlife, Chicken Wings, Bars
text:
This place is a hoot. Like any owl, it's all about the wings, and like any owl, your eyes will pop out. Because like any sexist establishment, Hooters only hires ridiculously good looking women, usually with massive natural breasts or preferably fake ones. They all wear low cut tops to show off said assets, and tiny little spandex booty shorts that make them basically look like Playboy Bunnies mark II, or strippers, both of which look fantastic and are awesome, but are also completely derogatory towards women and set us back about half a century with regards to equal rights.

I came here against my will. It's true. My last will and testament explicitly states: "Do not drag my corpse to Hooters." Now you know. The people that brought me here (Jacob and his friend that does not want to be named), who live in TN, will give it a 6 out of 5 every time for the drinks, the wings, and the girls. One of them also claims they have the best burgers in America. I could not disagree more - the burgers are boring and bland. The wings are good, not great. The girls are spectacular... Jacob was too busy staring at the meat. On the burger, I mean. Typical Jacob though. I think he had the best case of beer goggles (for burgers) in America. 

My opinion of the food was very different from my friends. The wings, I liked. I've been to maybe 10 Hooters in my life and the wings are always pretty good, and don't taste microwaved. However, I got to try a bite of the burger, and it was horribly overcooked. The only saving grace of my visit here other than the nice wings, was our server. She was so lovely and adorable. But the Hooters girls almost always are. However, the bill was insane. And I think generally you tip Hooters waitresses twice as much as you'd usually tip, because they're wearing all that stuff (or that lack of stuff) for you, so it ends up costing way more than you'd expect. Drinks aren't cheap either.

So, given that it is a corporate chain, it has to score 1, 2 or 3. Given that it has amazing beautiful women who are so nice, it scores 3. But given that it is so sexist and slightly overpriced, Hooters is back down to a 2.

I was friends with several Hooters girls in college. I found out that working there is sort of like being a Cheerleader. You can consider it along similar lines, because the employees do. I have to say this particular Hooters has some really amazing women. And like every other Hooters it has good wings, so it's worth a visit. Except that it is an evil chain that is taking over food and putting all the families out of business.

Which means it scores a lowly 2 and you should steer well clear. But if any of the girls from this location are interested, I'm not doing anyone, I mean, thing, next Tuesday night.

text: If u could give 0 stars I would! A very disappointed and dissatisfied loyal customer! I went in to redeem what was promised to me by the manager and everyone looked at me as if I was crazy! They refused to honor what was promised in totality and on top of that one of the employees talked trash in Spanish as if I couldn't understand what she was saying! Needless to say, I will not be back to this location and I wouldn't advise anyone else to spend their hard earned money there either!

name: Domino's Pizza
categories: Restaurants, Food Delivery Services, Food, Chicken Wings, Sandwiches, Pizza
text: If I could leave a 0 star I would. I ordered two medium pizzas tonight and upon following the app it said my pizza was done and it was on the app as finished for 40 min before I called to check the status, when I finally did call the original person I spoke with told me they only had 10 drivers and were busy and actually said I quote "you may get cold pizza, you may not." In literal shock I asked to speak to the manager when he got on the phone I told him my issue with the customer service and he said "the pizza sits on a heating rack so it can't get cold." I explained that's fine I asked why I'm being told my pizza could be cold, and he said to a co worker to call and cancel my order. I'm frustrated because I didn't want to cancel my order I wanted to check on my order status and it turned into this whole ordeal I now feel compelled to write a review on. Michael the gm of the Fairview and five mile store is the MOST unprofessional person I've ever spoke with, and yes I realize it's just dominos but where do we draw the line people? I just wanted pizza and now it's canceled (without me asking it to be) so I'm hungry grouchy and nursing my 5 week old without a stomach full of pizza. Irritated.

If you want cold ice and Pepsi with some fizz to it however, this is your place.

name: KFC
categories: Chicken Wings, Restaurants, Fast Food, Chicken Shop
text:
I decided to try out their new $5 meal.  

This is a slightly dated, worn looking restaurant.  But don't let that deter you.  The servers were friendly and as prompt as possible. Who ever did the design/work flow never worked there though.  The workers were constantly going all around to complete not only my order but ALL the orders.  

The chicken was good and fresh.  The portion of mashed potatoes was more than enough.  In fact, I was very full for $5.

I haven't been to a KFC in ages but if I go again I'll go here.

name: Sbarro
categories: Pizza, Italian, Restaurants
text: I'm very disappointed. Sbarro has been a pizza place I've gone to since I was a kid. There was only one lady working up front, she was sweet, red hair, just a little different, but she didn't seem to be able to manage very well up front by herself. She was putting in 3 orders at a time, then coming to the cash register for nearly 10 minutes for those 3 to pay, then would go and get the pizza out of the oven that was burnt and black as ever, probably for having it in there too long. I'm not the kind of a person to write a bad review, but felt I had to. My husband and I were very disappointed. The people before me had pizza way more burnt than mine, and that's because it was in the oven "warming up" much longer. Like literally black - no red sauce color, no yellow cheese color. Surprised they didn't complain in front of her. Once I got my food, I didn't say anything because I knew if I did, I'd have to wait all the time I did in that line again, and possibly only to get another piece of pizza the same amount of burnt it was the first time around. This experience concerns me and has kinda left a bad taste in my mouth and taken away my interest to want to eat there again. It would be nice to remind staff that putting it in the oven is not meant to cook the pizza, because these pieces of pizza looked like they had literally been cooked 3 times. They need to remember that it's just meant to warm it up.

name: Steak n Shake
categories: Restaurants, American (New), Burgers, Steakhouses, Fast Food, American (Traditional), Breakfast & Brunch, Diners
text:
Dream Girl and I had been across the street at Darrell Waltrip's getting her car serviced. It was about 1 PM and we had thought about going to 55 South (would that we had), but opted for Steak 'n' Shake as it was more convenient, or so we thought.

We waited for about ten minutes to be seated while servers slunk around avoiding eye contact and chit-chatting in the area where they pick up food. Finally we saw a tall young man begin to clear tables and folks were seated. Just enough tables were cleared to allow the backlog to be seated.

That same man was our server and he did a fairly adequate job of getting our drinks and taking our orders. Our food finally came and DG's steakburger with bacon was cold as were the fries on the plate. I had the footlong hot dog which was OK. We were never checked on till we were just about to leave when our server asked if I wanted more sweet tea and if I wanted it in a go-cup. The tea was good so I did, No question to see if DG wanted more Coca-Cola.

It took several minutes for a sullen someone to come to the cash register where customers waited patiently to pay for their meals. As we stood there we realized that our feet were sticking to the tile floor; it was dirty and our soles crackled as we lifted them. Hot water and a good scrub would be its only salvation.

Each of us has eaten in many Steak 'n' Shakes through the years and enjoyed burgers, milkshakes, and chili (I even have the recipe for that  tasty dish), but will never eat at this one again.

Morale among the employees is shot and there are no smiles. After management (if such exists) gets the place cleaned up and functioning, they should give all employees $20 and send them to Chick-fil-a to see how a real place is run!

name: KFC
categories: Chicken Wings, Chicken Shop, Fast Food, Restaurants
text: Do not use their online ordering. I made an order online at this location today and first of all, their website sucks. Second of all, I ordered online because I do not want to get off and have contact with anyone in the establishment, I mean we are in the middle of a pandemic. After waiting for about 10-15 minutes at the drive thru, I'm told at the speaker that mobile orders are required to be picked up inside the establishment. She says the front counter needs to confirm it. If I wanted to get off and go inside, I would not have ordered online. Once I'm inside the establishment, they all have a bad attitude. I don't understand why they offer contactless ordering and contactless payment if you have to get off your vehicle and touch door handles and counters that have been touched by dozens of people in the last hour? On top of that, someone placed a grub hub order and when the delivery person came to pick it up, he was told that they were out of what the person ordered, why wouldn't they let the person ordering know? And why not address it with them instead of the delivery person? I will definitely not be returning here unless they change this ridiculous policy!

name: Chili's
categories: Nightlife, Restaurants, American (New), Tex-Mex, Bars, American (Traditional)
text:
We were greeted by a hostess or should I say host?  Anyway it's a 20 to 30 minute wait. 
That's okay because I'm working on my patience ...... it's a virtue.
So we got a seat.  It's a shame that so many businesses are suffering from Covid and some won't survive this pandemic.
I had the old timer hamburger plate and a cup of chicken Enchilada soup for my appetizer.
The soup was very thick and didn't taste fresh.
My husband had chicken wings with the bone in, dipped in  mango habanero sauce, Caesar salad, and. Triple Dipper, which is chicken nuggets, chicken strips and boneless wings with what ever sauce you want and ranch/ blue cheese dressings and celery sticks.
Overall the food 1 star
Server ( which he mere said his name) 1 star 
Friendliness and knowledge of the menu. 1 star.  As I m mentioned above about Covid this restaurant had only the bar area open.
The whole other side of the restaurant was closed.  :-(  The bar area had tables open........BUT, the were full of dirty dishes and glasses.  And the seats at the bar as well.
The Host was running around trying to clean tables and greet people at the same time.  I seen 1 bartender and Maybe 2 servers in the bar area.  I guess 1 cook as well.  Because it took a little while to get our order out but it also was a good crowd of people around 8:00 PM.   Please send help to this Chili's, please!

name: China Jade

text:
First visit there today - mixed impression.  I'm generally not a fan of buffets but the food was decent.  Service not too bad for a buffet - plates were cleared and water glasses refilled promptly.  Two big turnoffs for me:
-  Terrible traffic flow around the buffet 'island'
-  Food containers were tiny on the buffet.  The rice pot was constantly empty.  In a Chinese place?  WTF???  Seriously, if you're going to have a limited number of buffet selections, at least keep it stocked!

The big plus was the price - very cheap.

text: Upon entering this dimly lit peanut infested chain restaurant, I was greeted with lackluster defeated facial expressions. Rather than having one of these souless hosts take me to a table, I decided to keep my joy and walk myself to the bar. I was greeted by a young beverage savior known as Morgan. As she poured an all american L.I.T., I look around the room and spot sadness in the eyes and more so the hearts of all the servers around. Identifiable looks of "when will this world take me?" And back to Morgan. Literally killing the drink game. As I throw more peanuts on the ground and down a handful of mozzarella sticks, I know everything in this world is gonna be alright. Thanks Morgan for making this a truly exceptional experience, regardless of working around defeated meat popsicles.

name: Panda Express
categories: Fast Food, Restaurants, Ethnic Food, Food, Specialty Food, Chinese
text:
I came expecting okay food and blergh service and was not disappointed. 

Came in at like 5:45, it was fairly quiet. No long line like last time. Downside was that either they just didn't prep anything or I came right after a huge rush, as they were missing two of the five items I wanted (Broccoli Beef and Mixed Veggies). Given this particular location, I would consider both possibilities equally likely. Because there was no one behind me, I opted to wait. 

In the four minutes it took for them to get a fresh batch of veggies and broccoli beef, they forgot every single request I made for my order. They packed up my order to-go (I told them I was dining in), and they put the broccoli beef into a separate container (I told them they could just pile it into the box). They were also about to walk away until I flagged them down for a pair of chopsticks. This immediately became problematic as the broccoli beef was set upside down in the bag, causing the gravy to leak out onto everything. Again, I ate this in, so it was about six paces to the table to unpack the contents of the bag. There was little to no possibility of the contents jostling sufficiently to create the spillage.

I will reiterate my points from my first review. The food is fine. It's super cheap Chinese fare made with expediency in mind. You can create a pretty healthy yet flavorful plate for a reasonable price. It's this particular location that's an issue as apparently they managed to hire the least competent folks in Tucson. I've had no issues with the location in Park Place Mall, which is my other primary location, but I go to this store only because it's on the way home from work when I'm at my hungriest.

name: Dunkin'
categories: Food, Restaurants, Donuts, Coffee & Tea
text: This is the worse dunkin donuts in the world. Their service, drinks, and food are so bad that I go out of my  way to drive 10 mins to the next Dunkin. I have ordered 10 different drinks there. Hot and cold. The drinks are never liquid. They put so much syrup in it that it's consistency is that of a syrup. Even if you ask for an unsweetened drink they still manage to put corn syrup or caramel or vanilla swirl in it. THE WORSE PART- when you tell them they made your drink wrong they get mad at you. ??!? Please make it make sense. The lady that works there almost 24/7 is so rude. I genuinely have never met anyone like that before. She gives dirty looks and talks with a nasty attitude. Every English muffin sandwich or bagel I have ever gotten from here has been burnt. Not just burnt, charred. And it's not just me, I've asked at least 5 other friends that live in the area and they all tell me that they also intentionally avoid that dunkin because they've had so many bad experiences. They also drive 10 mins to the next one. Please don't come to this dunkin. Do yourself a favor and drive to any other dunkin. Or go home and make yourself a coffee.

name: Buffalo Wild Wings
categories: Bars, Sports Bars, Nightlife, Restaurants, American (Traditional), Chicken Wings
text: This is a chain restaurant. The atmosphere and the menu are the same at every BW3's.  With that said, I have never been disappointed with the food or the service at this location.  Maybe I've just lucked-out.  Or, maybe it's because I try to stay away when I know the place is going to be packed to the gills. We pretty much just stick with bone-in wings and baskets of potato wedges and draft beer when we eat here.  Their wings are always cooked perfectly and their huge variety of sauces are all great. The only complaint I would have is that the wings seem to vary in size too often. I've yet to have bad or mediocre service here. It seems most of the waitstaff are younger but they've always been on the ball and been courteous. BW3's is close to our house and always a great place to go with our kids & family or a large group of friends.

name: Steak n Shake
categories: American (New), Diners, Fast Food, Restaurants, Burgers, Breakfast & Brunch, American (Traditional)
text: Let's face it. It's a Steak 'n Shake. The food is what it is, and that's all it is. The chili is classic, the fries are epic, and the burgers, come on. My review has very little to do with the food. My review is the staff only. First of all, my friend and I walk in and there a line for seating. Plenty of open chairs, but no one is seating guests. Kind of odd. So we decide to sit at the bar. At this point we realize that half the line is actually waiting to pay, and the other half waiting for seats. The cook is looking around for someone, even some of the younger staff are starting to freak out, and yet nothing is moving. Finally, the cook just about flips and runs back to find the manager. She comes out, and hurriedly starts checking people out while flagging down someone to seat people. She takes our order quickly, and disappears. This is the last we see her. Our food comes in average time, but only because the cook is pretty much forcing waitresses to work. Meanwhile, they're all almost exclusively on the phones. We eat, but something happens that just shouldn't. I say with an empty drink glass the entire time. That. Should. Never. Happen. So, we finally get checked out, and because I didn't get any refills, I ask for a to-go cup. This takes another 20 minutes. I don't know why, but Steak 'n Shake just needs to re haul to find ways to get faster.

name: Southtown Hyundai
categories: Automotive, Used Car Dealers, Breakfast & Brunch, Car Dealers, Auto Repair, Restaurants
text:
To be honest, Hyundai Southtown contain a lot of professional and friendly individuals, however for my experience there with Micheal Castro as a sales associate, The deal we worked out was no where near the total amount I had to pay (I had to pay an extra $2250). He is a great sales associate some may say and I would agree to a certain extent since I found his car knowledge to lack proficiency. In other words, he may know how to sale a car perhaps but can only sales talk you into purchasing one with very basic information about the car, which may portray him as a knowledgeable sales man. Quick tip: Ask for all the details up front with Micheal Castro (from my experience). Do not work out a deal before he shows you the AMVIC and made you aware of all the car conditions. That way, the deal may be reasoned efficiently. On the other hand, Genevieve's patience amazed me. Kudos to her. 
P.S. My experience may differentiate from some others and this is not to say that the salesman is a bad one. I am simply telling the truth. At the end of the day, he made the mistake and I still had to pay the extra $2250, which was not the deal we originally worked out. He did not advocate for me, regarding this extra amount I had to pay. That is what I find shameful.

name: Sonic Drive-In
categories: Restaurants, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Burgers, Fast Food, Food
text:
I have had the absolute worst customer
Experience ever. I frequent the Sonic at broadway and Harrison in Tucson, AZ as it is really close to my home. Who doesn't love a Route 44 on a hot day. Today, after a few long and trying day ( I work I  healthcare, running a medical office, and found out that one of my favorite patient had passed away from the Corona virus) my two girls and I stopped at sonic to get three drinks and three ice creams to enjoy after dinner and hopefully bring a little joy after a really rough and trying day. I arrived at approximately 6:00pm, pulled into stall #3 and ordered our items. I paid with credit card at the stall. I watch as the car hops ran around delivery food, drinks and ice creams to the car near by. At 6:20pm, I press the red button again and asked if we had been forgotten, as we were waiting, and had now seen cars that arrived after us get their orders. Kevin answered the button, asked me what stall we were in, and then said, we are making your blasts, they will be right out. No apology for the delay. We continued to wait. At 6:30pm, ten minutes later still nothing and the car that had pulled up right next to us, got their items, which included ice cream and drinks. So I pressed the button again. This time a female answered, at this point I have been waiting for 30 minutes and am not very happy, as I have Chinese take-out which is now cold because we have been waiting for so long. She tells me that they has issues with the ice Cream machine. I asked for a manager to come out to my car. I also explained that if there was an issue with the ice cream machine, I should have been told. And she stayed that she was very sorry, the order was on them and it would be right out. Another 10 minutes went buy, and another customers order was brought out. I left. Let me be clear, this is not the first time I have waiting for 30-40 minutes for an order at this sonic. The last time this happened, I emailed corporate without ever recieving a response.
I don't except anything. To come from this either. But I want you to know thst because of this, a family that loved Sonic, frequented several
Location in town, will no longer be patrons of any of your locations. 

I called the store to talk to the manager. Kevin answered the phone. I said I would like to talk to the manager. He stated he was the manager. I asked for the name of the general store manager and he said it was him. I said well I want to make sure I am refunded. He started to talk over me every time I tried to talk she kept trying to tell me the order was ready and coming out. I was trying to tell him that I had left and he kept talking over me. Unfortunately, I got angered by us disrespect, especially because I find out the I had already talked to the and her before, and he had not apologized for the issues the first time. I did begin to tell because he kept rudely talking over me. He was snarky and had a bad attitude, and the saying goes, treat other they way you wish to be treated, well Kevin was being rude, ungrateful and unapologetic for this absolutely in acceptable issues happening at his restaurant. Now let me be clear, I am an office manager, I understand how trying it can be and attempted to keep my cool as much as possible. And note that my husband is the general manager of a local restaurant in town and I understand how it is. I don't know if Kevin was having a bad day himself, but unfortunately, he needs to know that as a manager, he needs to handle business appropriately, regardless of his personal issues. I have to everyday. I will let all my friends know about this issue. I hope the Kevin will be made aware of this issue, although I doubt that he will care as he didn't seem to tonight either. I just want to through one last thing put there, Kevin needs to be grateful that he had a restaurant to go to and a job right now. He should be grateful for every customer coming to his store to support and keep them open in the current time. There was no appreciate today.

name: Popeyes Louisiana Kitchen
categories: Food, Chicken Wings, Restaurants, Fast Food
text:
One of the worst establishments I have ever visited. Been here more than one occasion and each time it has been ever so disappointing.
First they got my order wrong and overcharged me. Then they got the physical order wrong...and ran out of the boneless wings. We ordered green beans and mashes potato sides. We all got fries. When I tried to explain the mistake the cashier was taking the whole boxes away. I said if youre out of boneless wings, why are you taking my wings. I don't want the fries but I don't want your hands in my food. So the manager came and just told her to leave the fries and give me the correct sides. Oh and the sign outside needs updating. It still had the promotion before (red sticks)the current promotion (boneless wings). 
The bathrooms are gross. I once saw one of the food tubs under the sink collecting water. Drink machine kept running out of drinks. Tables we're all dirty. Trash was overflowing.
Added bonus, its very warm inside. I don't know why I keep forgetting not to come here. The one on Gentilly blvd is equally bad.
I hope it gets better...but in my experience over time...it hasn't.

name: Taco Bell
categories: Restaurants, Fast Food, Tex-Mex, Breakfast & Brunch, Mexican, Tacos
text: I have my moments of going to a Taco Bell and every time I've gone it's been great. Few weeks ago I went during lunch rush and I got the $5 box like always. The soda was flat, my burrito was "soupy," cheese was cold... it was tragic! The burrito ended up dropping out of the wrapping and onto my pants, talk about a mess! Need be I expressed my concerns to a manager and he helped out greatly, but upon returning for a comp, the workers there were rude... Thanks guys! I guess I just haven't hit a jackpot day there. Definitely double check your meals!

text: We ordered online on the day of Football Sunday so I was prepared to wait at least an hour and a half or more for the food to be ready. I get it, it's football Sunday and they're busy but that doesn't give them the right to mess up an order that I paid for! It seemed as if they didn't even TRY to make the food good. I don't think I'll ever be going back there. I wish I could post pics of how terrible and dry the wings looked but they ended up in the trash. So disappointed that I paid money for them.

name: Quiznos
categories: Restaurants, Sandwiches, Delis, Fast Food
text: If you've never been to the Nashville airport then you don't know that it is long in the tooth! It looks like it's getting a makeover because it sorely does need one! My guy and I were on our way home from a two week driving tour of the Southeast. We started in Nashville and we ended in Nashville and we just loved it! However even though our hotel gave breakfast, we had to leave earlier than the hotel was starting breakfast to make our plane. We headed off to the airport and didn't expect to find the best things for breakfast, But we didn't expect to find what we found either! There is nothing but Starbucks and a couple other fried up restaurants with all disgusting food. Finally we came across Quiznos in terminal C. Thank God we did! They actually had egg and cheese sandwiches, bacon egg and cheese sandwiches, ham egg and cheese sandwiches, and different kinds of breads. Nothing fried! Hooray! I had just the plain egg with tomatoes on wheat bread. My guy had ham egg and cheese on wheat bread. Very very good, healthy, and just what we were looking for! Can't wait for the next trip to Nashville when they hopefully have added more healthy restaurants and better choices!

name: Szechuan Village
categories: Imported Food, Ethnic Food, Food, Chinese, Restaurants, Specialty Food
text: I read some other reviews for this place so I thought I should leave mine. I've been getting takeout here for many, many years. While I no longer live in Edmonton, I do visit almost monthly and I get takeout here almost every time I come. I only wish I could find Chinese takeout this good in Arizona where I now live. The food for me has always fresh and hot, and is always absolutely delicious. We've had so many family gatherings with this food and everyone raves about how good it is. Now, this is not authentic chinese cuisine, any place with chicken balls on the menu will not be (I've been to China many times) This is classic American style Chinese food that we all grew up eating, and this place does it as good or better than anywhere I've ever been. I crave this place. I've never actually eaten in the restaurant, but have picked up takeout at least 50 times. The dinner for two is really two meals for three people. It's not a fancy place, but it's good, cheap, excellent Chinese takeout, and tonight's meal was excellent as usual.

text: Went to carls jr on Kitzke in reno early October. We went through 3 times. We ordered the Big Carl combo with normal cries and the Jalapeo burger combo with krisscut fries. The fries were cold and the cheese looked like someone wiped their nose with it. We went back and they said they would fix it. It was back there for 3 mins and came back and tossed my order through the window at us. I thought it was a fresh order it was the same one. I went back said I wanted my money back. They gave us back the money and the male worker told us "Now get the F*** Out of here". By the way this was all caught on video I've tried to contact corporate and the restaurant owner in the last 3 weeks and neither will reply. Way to go carls jr I'd rather eat McDonald's then go back to you guys

text:
Well Wendy's...............I'm proud of you.  While "never" is a long time, I actually visited this location (drive thru) today as I had a gift card.  

Pros:   
I was in and out of there in under 90 seconds.
The gentleman at the drive thru window was super friendly.
The food was out quick.
The food was hot.
The food was correct!

I ordered a medium Baconator meal with a diet Coke.  The only down side to this specific experience was the overload of salt on the fries, but I'm not counting that against them.  This Wendy's location on Parkside Drive has come a LONG way since previous experiences and I'm really hopeful for their future!    Good job!

name: Pollo Tropical
categories: Food, Chicken Wings, Specialty Food, Chicken Shop, Fast Food, Ethnic Food, Restaurants, Caribbean, Latin American
text:
On the west coast there is a restaurant called "El Pollo Loco" which I miss dearly and I found this place on yelp and it looked pretty similar so I decided to give it a try.  I visited on 5/22/17 around 6pm and went through the drive thru.  $12.82 got me a 1/2 chicken meal and a kid's meal.  Their menu is more Caribbean influenced than El Pollo Loco and they have bowls, salads, grilled chicken meals, sandwiches, and wraps.   

I got the $6.99 1/2 chicken meal which came with two sides and a roll.  I chose black beans and white rice for my two sides. The grilled chicken was so good...The skin was crispy and the inside was moist and flavorful.  It had a wonderful salty charred flavor!  The sides were prepared well and hot and fresh.  Ask for their mustard curry sauce...it's creamy and divine for dipping the grilled chicken into.  I poured a bunch over my rice....it's so darn good.  

For my boy I got the $4.99 kid's grilled breast strips meal with came with one side, a roll, a drink, and a guava bar.  For his side I chose the corn which was a bit dried out but he's only 2 and could care less.  It was a lot of food for the price!  The guava bar....oh my goodness that guava bar...I've been dreaming about that guava bar all day.  Imagine tart and sweet guava paste sandwiched between two moist pieces of delicious cake....incredible!  I took a bite and handed it to my son and when I went to get it back he snatched it away and finished it. 

I can't wait to go back!  I liked it a lot.

name: Dookys Chase's
categories: Restaurants, Food, Desserts, Breakfast & Brunch, Cajun/Creole
text: They are located in front of the security checkpoint. With the history of the restaurant and watching them on the food network and travel channel, I was super excited to try Dooky chase restaurant prior to leaving back home. I ordered two orders of 3 piece chicken with French fries  for $19 each order. I ordered it to-go since I was waiting for my flight and was going to eat it while waiting for my flight. It took about 25 mins for them to fry it, once I opened up my order, I noticed that they got my order wrong and I got one order of fried chicken and a steak. I tried calling them and looking up the address but nothing was listed on the website and didn't have anything on the main website for the other location. It's frustrating to spend money to get the wrong order and not to be able to go back and make it right since you have to check in to the airport again. The chicken was moist and delicious, and the steak was so so.  The management should update the website and have phone numbers listed to help their customers
