name: Buffalo Wild Wings
categories: Specialty Food, Sports Bars, Burgers, American (Traditional), Food, Bars, Nightlife, Restaurants, Meat Shops, Chicken Wings
text: After standing at the door for a while waiting to be seated we were greeted by a very unfriendly woman who told us we can sit wherever we want. The place was pretty empty. It didn't take long for the waitress to come over and get our drink order and we explained to her that we needed to be out in an hour because we were meeting up for a tour. We gave our food order with our drink order to expedite things. While waiting, the waitress never came back to the table. We kept trying to get her attention but we could not. After 40 minutes of waiting with empty drinks I finally walked over to where she was standing and asked her if she knew about how much longer it might be. She said that the kitchen was putting the food on the tray right now. After waiting another five minutes I had to say excuse me rather loudly to get her attention as she was walking by. This was met with an annoyed look from her.I asked her if we could go ahead and get the checks to start paying since we needed to eat and run. Another five minutes went by and the food came out. At this point we had 10 minutes to eat, pay and get down the street to our meet up. I asked her if we could go ahead and have boxes brought since we did not expect the food to take 50 minutes to come out. She said "it only took 20 minutes for the food to come out but I'm not gonna argue it." I am always extremely friendly with wait staff because I know of the garbage that they have to deal with on a daily basis but this young lady was very rude. She spent a lot of time talking to the table across the restaurant full of young men and had no time to check on us. I will definitely never be going back.

name: Geno's Steaks
categories: Sandwiches, Cheesesteaks, Steakhouses, Restaurants
text:
I live in Philadelphia and therefore, I have tasted a real cheesesteak. Several, I have even lazily made one at home it's a simple formula a fresh amoroso long roll, cheese of your choice I prefer provolone as the cheese steak gods intended, as "whiz" is not a real food and therefore is not going to be acknowledged as cheese moving forward in this conversation. You then add meat, specifically thin sliced juicy ribeye. Some people like onions and peppers I like fried onions on top. The rest is up to you.

Pats and Genos share this review. Look at the formula! I waited a very long time outside for you Genos at least Pats disappointment was faster! Also, I don't like peppers if I ask for fried onions thats what I mean, it's not a combo. Finally tell your friggin cook the meat should be juicy, I felt like I was biting into a jerky sandwich are your kidding me?! My bodega on 4th and Jefferson makes better cheesesteaks than you and that's on the Birds . I gave you your five stars to keep tourists out of the North but I couldn't let it be left unsaid.

name: Riliberto's Fresh Mexican Food
categories: Mexican, Restaurants
text:
Ordered for delivery. Burrito wrapped in foil, a box for the tacos and a box for my side of fries. Bunch of 1oz salsa containers on the side. Overall solid meal for the price

Carne asada burrito was tasty, flavorful, and the meat was juicy - not dry here. Savory with the filling and burrito held together well. I also received red and green salsa which complimented well. The red salsa has enough zing that the heat builds! Thought that it would be a little bigger size given that it was $10. Would rate 4.5/5

The corn tortillas for the tacos were well made and with two of them the juices didn't rip the tortilla easily. Solid serving of meat per taco given price.
-Al pastor taco was my favorite of the 4 tacos I ordered. Highly recommend - Rate 5/5
-Carne asada was so dry in the taco, it was average when doused in salsa. Rate 2.5/5
-One Cabeza taco was super tender and good, second taco had some rubbery texture meat pieces unable to chew. Ideally should should be a 4/5 but inconsistent meat texture. 
-The French fries here are skinny and super plain. Only tasted decent with ranch I had at home. Feel free to skip the fries here. Rate 2/5

name: Panera Bread
categories: Sandwiches, Soup, American (Traditional), Coffee & Tea, Restaurants, Food, Bakeries, Salad
text:
This Panera is just not great. We ordered to go, and the first thing we noticed was my butternut squash soup and tomato guts, (presumably from my husband's sandwich, but who knows?) were all over the bag. It just got worse from there. I'd ordered the 2 item combo with the roast beef panini sandwich, and I've had it before at the Panera on Oracle where it was my favorite thing. But at this Panera, it was burnt bread, a small pile of meat at one end and not enough of the cheese and sauce. The soup, which I've always loved in the past, tasted like someone decided to improve the recipe by adding tons of sugar. My husband's sandwich had absolutely no condiments on it, totally dry. Again, he's ordered that item at the other Panera and enjoyed it.

We also got a dozen bagels to go. Won't do that again. There's a reason they're only $9.99 for a dozen. They're rolls with holes, not bagels.

All in all, I can't say we'll be back to that location, but we'll definitely go back to the one on Oracle.

name: IHOP
categories: Restaurants, American (New), American (Traditional), Breakfast & Brunch, Burgers
text:
After a nasty encounter with the hostesses of Sabrina's and a heart-wrenchingly long line at Honey's, my honey & I decided to throw caution to the wind.  Located the closest IHOP and made a bee line to Aramingo Ave.  It was around 2ish in the afternoon on a Saturday or Sunday, and to our delight, we walked in and got a table right away.  Sadly, our naive happiness could not last.  We were seated right next to the bathroom where an employee was diligently swishing around sickening bleach water.  You know, the kind you see Septa maintenance sloshing around the subway with a dark gray mop.

We asked to sit a little further away from this nightmare, and we were alright for a few minutes before the smell found us.  Again.  On the bright side, we had a bizarrely terrific server, and the sight of all the happy northeast families eating highly processed foods around us gave me a warm fuzzy feeling inside.  But at the end of the day, IHOP is just a big cafeteria with that kind of climate and that kind of food.  We knew what we were getting ourselves into, and we wanted it -- but not the weapons of chemical warfare emanating from the bathroom.  IHOP in the hood is IHOP in the hood, but damn it guys, do you have to kill us while we're there!?

name: Tucson Marriott University Park
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Restaurants, Hotels, Venues & Event Spaces
text:
Worst. Marriott. Ever....

From the moment you walk in, you are overwhelmed with a "damp" smell - strange. 

The bar selection and bartender were great. I added 4 stars for this, but they were swiftly taken away.

Restaurant food was good... maybe a little pretentious for Tucson, but done well. 

Where the bar/restaurant excelled, the hotel quickly took away....

After enjoying my dinner and drinks, I stopped at the desk to ask for a wakeup call... all was well until a minute or so after getting to my room I was greeted with a knock at my door for some fresh towels..

After that was settled, I tried turning on my TV to relax and go to sleep... nope, no TV.  Had to call to desk to have that fixed. Thankfully he didn't bring more towels and fixed it. 

Time for bed now and I'm not putting faith in my requested wakeup call...

name: Chili's
categories: Nightlife, American (Traditional), Bars, Restaurants, Tex-Mex
text: Was craving their Cajun chicken pasta last night so my boyfriend and I headed out for a date. As soon as I walked in around 9pm I see a broom and dust pan filled with trash sitting in front of the hostess station. The restaurant is trashed and empty and the hostess is nowhere to be found until she suddenly pops up from sitting in a booth to seat us. As we sit we look over the menu, the waitress comes over to take our drink order so we order two waters with lemon. She returns with two waters, no lemon. She asks us what we'd like to eat, were not sure yet so she walks away.. This is when she started to get impatient.. She didnt seem like she wanted to wait on us or give us time to look over their menu - she also never asked us if we had any questions. We finally order 2 margaritas, she asks to see ID so I hand her my passport since I lost my DL 2 weeks prior. The waitress tells me my passport is expired, which is impossible because I just returned from South America 2 months prior. I tell her she's looking at it wrong and she tells me that she's not but that she will get her manager. Then she throws my boyfriends ID at him on the table. After sitting there for 5 minutes, no manager comes over so we leave. Before walking out of the door I asked the hostess to please get her manager. She goes to get her manager and our waitress walks over to me as were standing in front of the door to tell me that she can't serve me alcohol with an expired passport. She clearly never consulted her manager. So, I get out my passport AGAIN to show her the date she was referring to was the date of issue. The date of expiration is underneath it. She didn't want to hear it so she walked away from me before I could show her. Being very rude. The manager comes over and I tell him the whole story, he apologizes. We go to the Chili's in tri city and have a lovely meal. End of story..., I will not be returning to the Largo Mall Chili's for dinner ever again. I've had great experiences during lunch. They need to get rid of their rude waitress and lazy hostess.

Then the street tacos I ordered were cold and  completely dried out. I will not order from here ever again!!  Way too much money for such poor quality!

name: Applebee's Grill + Bar
categories: American (Traditional), Bars, Sports Bars, Restaurants, Chicken Wings, Nightlife, Burgers, Steakhouses
text: I was not impressed. I work in the restaurant industry myself and am a server as well. But from the minute we were seated after waiting we were not greeted for about 15 minutes not afford drinks not acknowledged. Once we were I immediately thought I should just order food now so the girl does not forget about us. I understand it was busy but in that case I believe it's always your responsibility to send someone over or to at least give us a heads up you'll be over soon. The atmosphere was not well cleansed my friend needed a charging outlet which we tried to look for under the table we found left over trash and a knife. The food was disgusting overall I was not high on expectations but not was I that low either. I will not be returning. Please do better.

name: The Blue Note
categories: Bars, Restaurants, American (Traditional), Airport Lounges, Nightlife, Sports Bars
text:
You're not going to find anything cheap when it comes to food and drink at an airport.  The best one can hope for is a relaxing atmosphere and quick service.  This place succeeded at both.

I had approximately an hour before my flight.  It was self seating, and I found a table by the large windows overlooking the airfield. I ordered a Goose IPA and within minutes my server brought it out.  

I enjoyed my cold beverage and relaxing time.  I ordered and paid via my phone's camera scanning the bar code on the mini instructions placed on each table.  My server was prompt and efficient.  The pint cost $10.95.  Like I said, not cheap, but that's airports for you.  I would definitely return.

name: Buffalo Wild Wings
categories: Nightlife, Restaurants, Barbeque, Chicken Wings, Bars, Sports Bars, American (Traditional)
text: I love this Buffalo Wild Wings! I'm visiting Tucson for the weekend & went here today for a lunch date. The staff (especially Stephanie P.) was great & friendly. The service was exceptionally good as well. We ordered the House Sampler with boneless wings, nachos, mozzarella sticks & onion rings, along with a Long Island iced tea, screwball (peanut butter whiskey) shots & iced tea. Also, a grilled Buffalo chicken salad. The apps came out within about 7mins, and it honestly didn't seem like it since we were playing trivia and chatting it up with our server. Thumbs up Buffalo Wild Wings!

name: Geno's Steaks
categories: Sandwiches, Cheesesteaks, Steakhouses, Restaurants
text:
Dry dry dry dry dry meat. Yet Oily somehow.  I don't know how that combination is possible, but Geno's somehow has done it.  

Since Geno's is famous and tourists flock to the area,  I'd suggest eating at Pat's, which is right across the street.  Pat's is at least edible and isn't as oily.  

Oh yeah, and it helps that Pat's Cheesesteaks isn't xenophobic or racist...

name: Nugget Casino Resort
categories: Resorts, Event Planning & Services, Restaurants, Casinos, Arts & Entertainment, Party & Event Planning, Hotels, Venues & Event Spaces, Hotels & Travel
text: First the check in which was Nov 3 to 4 RM 2653. Anyways, check in was quick, but the clerk never explained anything about the hotel, restaurant s, pool, sports book, nothing, just handed me my c/c back and said the room number out loud. Which is a another no no.. room was ok. TV reception is terrible..as for the rest of the Casino, it's a dump,even with the remodel. I now know why this place is a hole. The cliental is at best seedy and dirty. If you like women with no teeth this is your spot.100% dump!!!. Now let's get to the worst buffet in the world.. it's here at the Nugget, first it took our waitress 5 times of asking to bring 2 ojs and 2 cokes and a coffee. The coffee never made until one of the cashier's got it. Also there is no ketchup or hot sauce or steak sauce on the table. We asked and it never arrived.. the food. Eggs Benedict were the worst I've ever had runny scrambled eggs undercooked sausage and dry bacon, pancakes were powedere and just try and find syurap for them. The bake goods like doughnuts and bread were just sitting under a light getting hard. The bagel I picked up you could have played hockey with it. The shrimp was the worst I've ever had. And just try and find the horseradish for your prime rib because the serving pan the had next it was oatmeal..this buffet is just a mess. I'm at home right now with diarrhea.. So Beware if you stay at the Nugget it's a ghetto horrible place with terrible food and service. STAY SOMEWHERE ELSE!!!!!

name: Hooters
categories: Sports Bars, Chicken Wings, Sandwiches, Restaurants, Burgers, Bars, American (Traditional), Nightlife
text: I don't know how this place has so many negative reviews. I've been there several times and was never disappointed. Let's start with the amazing view of the water. I always sit outside and enjoy looking for dolphins. The girls (servers/bartenders) have always been friendly and efficient. The food is great! My hubby and I always order their shrimp with sweet chili sauce and some hot wings. A pitcher of cold beer quenches our thirst. Have accidentally gone there on "Football Sundays." Each of their many tv's is broadcasting a game. It's a bit loud (main reason why we try to avoid sport bars on those days). The fans seem to have a blast and it's always been friendly and people kept it classy. Outside tvs do have a lot of glare, but there are plenty inside for those who really want to watch. Will be definitely back again and again.

name: Pho Hoa
categories: Restaurants, Vietnamese
text:
I would give this restaurant 3 stars but the dishes are filthy.  Not just stained but actual filth that you can scrape  with your spoon.  I found that rather revolting and mentioned it.  The restaurant just said it is an issue with the new bowls.  I understand that they are difficult to clean but they clear can be cleaned with a little effort.  Anyway, if dirty dishes gross you out, this restaurant is not for you.

That being said, the pho was pretty good though the noodles are mushy.  The broth was good, price reasonable-ish, meat portion above average (except very stingy with tendon).  This is my second time eating at this chain with mushy noodles so might not be a one off issue.  The price is a bit cheaper than some others but they charge for tea so I would say comparable.   If you don't like tea, this is a good deal.  Plus they have a nice combo: soup, green onion cake and a pop for $15.

Restaurant has a nice feel inside but booths are run down with worn and dirty benches.  

Service prompt with order and food delivery but after that good luck. We tried multiple times to get our waiters attention without success.  

It had a reasonable lunch timr crowd so it clearly has a good local following.

name: Starbucks
categories: Cafes, Coffee & Tea, Restaurants, Food
text: Another customer service fail today...I came thru on a Sunday morning around 11am to treat my auntie to a coffee and breakfast sandwhich as she was arriving from a long, overnight drive from Mexico. We walked into the establishment because the drive thru line was super long as usual. We walked up to the counter to order and weren't acknowledged for 3-5 minutes. Once we placed our order and stepped aside to wait, I observed a young man walk in with his young son. They stepped up to order and was immediately acknowledged by a barista that previously ignored me. I don't know why I continue to get shoddy service but of course, since Starbucks is my guilty pleasure, I will return.

name: Applebee's Grill + Bar
categories: American (Traditional), Bars, Steakhouses, Nightlife, Restaurants, Burgers, Sports Bars
text:
Where do I begin....if I had to describe my experience in one word it would be...sad.  Let me first say we usually do lunch. Lunch time has always been good to us but dinner had way too many problems that we won't be back. 

We were sat immediately by a friendly hostess. Salad was a little flat....just ok. Meals did come out in timely manner and piping hot. Problem came when my boyfriend got his chicken and shrimp meal. Waitress asked if he wanted the mushrooms and onions, he said yes.  It came out with (I'm not kidding) 2 slices of mushrooms....REALLY. Asked for more mushrooms and she had audacity to say it's extra. He told her he wasn't interested in paying extra for something that was already part of the meal. We asked to speak to a manager. 

Now let me tell you he was 1/2 done with his meal by time manager came out with mushrooms...which he hastily placed on table....now that I'm thinking about it don't think he even looked at us. Manager didn't ask why we asked to speak to a manger, just said here are you grilled mushrooms. We didn't ask for the manager because we wanted him to be our waiter...hell we had an issue.  The real problem came when we went to pay the bill and noticed a charge for .99. Of course we brought it to her attention. Do you know she had the nerve to say "oh I'll take it off your bill." Damn you could have done that in the first place. Not to mention she must have complained about us to the manager cause I could see both of them whispering and looking back at us...not like I give a damn. 

Did I forget to mention that the waitress never came back to check on us after she brought out our food; she only came back when it looked like we were done with our food and it was time to pay. Never mind I'm dying of dehydration because I have any empty cup in front of me.

name: Boston Pizza
categories: Italian, Pizza, Restaurants
text: I was in town from Winnipeg and I wasn't finished with work until almost midnight. I looked up this location and saw they were open until 1:00, so I thought it would be perfect to run to for a quick pizza and drink. When I arrived, an hour before close, the manager was shutting down all the VLT machines and leaning chairs against them, indicating the area was closed down for the night. Usually while I wait for my food I'll throw a few dollars in the machine, but it looked like thar wouldn't be the case. The bartender came from the back and asked for my order. I asked if there was a drink special - and was promptly told no. This seemed odd, as most BPs have something every night of the week, but I assumed being so close to the mall, maybe they didn't run specials. Either way I ordered my drink and my pizza. The bartender then went about her closing duties (again - still an hour before closing time) putting things away. The manager passed by me several times back and forth from the VLTs and never once made eye contact or acknowledged my presence (I was alone at the bar and there was two other tables of three in the lounge). The whole experience was definitely unwelcoming. I quickly ate my pizza when it arrived, and the bartender did ask if it was good after a few bites. Other than that, I settled up and headed out. I probably would have stayed for another drink or two, but it really felt like that wasn't what the staff wanted. It's pretty common knowledge that BP's food has decreased in quality and value in recent years, but their saving grace has always been decent drink specials and friendly staff - neither of which could be found at this location.

name: Manhattan Bagel
categories: Bagels, Food, Breakfast & Brunch, Sandwiches, Restaurants
text:
I don't understand this place.  It seems to change hands between management, ethnicities, and staff as often as daylight savings time switches on and off every year.  This time, a totally new crew.  Five people and one manager feverishly working and a mini-mob of customers in line.  All the workers behind the counters, which meant no one monitored the coffee thermos, a few of which had no coffee.  Call it to their attention and panic ensued.  

Once the coffee situation was adjusted, the place seemed to hum a bit better.  Got what I wanted quickly and left.  Eggs and ham on a toasted everything bagel, and one toasted whole wheat and double-cream cheese.  Not bad.  Just needs to get better.  No outside seating per se, even though there's plenty of room outside for that.    Overall:  Meh...

name: Domino's Pizza
categories: Pizza, Chicken Wings, Restaurants, Sandwiches
text:
AVOID AT ALL COSTS
By far the worst pizza I've had. Thin crust was not crunchy, olives were junk and salad was $6 for bad strands of lettuce and minimal cheese which looked horribly powdered. It came in a prepacked divider. Rip off. Not worth more than a dollar. 

Their knots were ok, and extremely unhealthy, but rest was crap.

I normally don't order from them or anyone else but good pizza like Grimaldi's, BJs or Mellow Mushroom but I hadn't gone grocery shopping and normally stock up on organic pizza from Publix or whole foods which btw is cheaper and tastier. But, this was the only place opened late. 

I never want dominoes again. It's just a reminder that corporate chains need to fall and get out the way. I rather pay for quality. Not preservatives and poison. 

Never Again!!! 

Calling card tomorrow to get refund! Waste of $30.

name: Kingston City Restaurant
categories: Restaurants, Caribbean
text:
Mixed results on delivery -- pickup or in-store dining may be better.

We ordered some things via GitHub. Some things were unavailable and others were changed after our order, so that wasn't great.

The entrees were fine; in both cases the meat was tender and falling off the bone (I think we got the BBQ chicken, which had a tasty, tangy sauce; and the stewed beef, which had decent flavor and good texture). Neither entree was exciting. Last Caribbean food I had was off the food trucks near 30th (a few years ago). Then, I was less hungry but the food tasted better, which says something. Usually Caribbean food knocks my socks off and makes me swoon. This food was merely "tasty".

The sides, which for me are usually the highlight of Caribbean food, were real disappointments. The rice & beans were dry, and the cabbage was boring; the yams were two sweet without enough spice. The plantains were so-so, not better than I could make if handed a plantain and a pot to cook it in.

All in all, a mostly "meh" experience, but I'm giving it 3 stars instead of 2 since the entrees were definitely better than average as far as delivery goes, just not better than average for Caribbean.

text: Does DQ no longer include toast with their chicken strip baskets? This is the second time in a row I've ordered the 4 piece basket and NOT received toast. Of course the other negative part (which I think everyone knows) is that their chicken strips are also insanely small compared to how they used to be. And lastly, my chocolate shake came with no whipped cream on top (guessing they were out?) and the shake itself tasted off compared to their tasty normal ones-- it almost tasted more like cocoa or something? Not a great experience tonight. I'm not one to leave a negative review after one trip, but it's been a few times now that have been negative. Just feel like DQ has really lowered their standards sadly.

name: Caf Central
categories: Sandwiches, American (New), Cafes, Asian Fusion, Breakfast & Brunch, Chinese, American (Traditional), Restaurants, Nightlife, Bars
text:
Lunch: Silver Legacy [Reno]

Dined here two weeks ago when we decided to take my mom to Reno on a day trip. Caf Central is located in the Silver Legacy at THE ROW. It was our first time dining here. It wasn't our first choice of place to eat but there was no wait in line so we went for it and we were seated immediately. Spacing between tables were good and complied with social distancing during Covid times. Staff wore masks.

We were actually seated in a booth and we were immediately tended to for our drink orders. Our waitress shortly came after to get our food orders. Mom and I decided to share a Chicken Alfredo meal. Husband ordered the Joe's Special (breakfast meal). Our food came in good time and the presentation was nice. 

Not the best Alfredo pasta I've tasted. The Chicken Alfredo was bland and the sauce was too runny. The two slices of garlic bread were placed on top of the sauce so half of the breads were soggy. Mom and I didn't finish it... it took the three of us to finish the plate. My hubby did not eat the hash brown that came with his meal... it was too oily. We enjoyed our glasses of Coke and refreshing lemonade, though.

We had a good waitress. She was attentive and friendly. It was unfortunate that the food was just mediocre. Maybe will try something else from the menu next time. 

Review #1964

name: Ms Mexicali Cantina
categories: Restaurants, Nightlife, Bars, Mexican, Food
text: Just awful. We went here for lunch today and were sorely disappointed by the woefully slow service (30 minutes to receive appetizers and over one hour to receive entrees), and a server who we rarely saw. She blamed the slow food delivery on having only one chef and a full roof deck, so we waited and waited and watied till our food arrived and our waters got refilled.  We ultimately found the food cold, waaay too salty, with overdone chicken and oily chimichanga. Then at the end of the meal we went up to check out the happening deck and found it beautiful but. . . .you guessed it. . . Dead empty. Poor form, dear server. By the way, we felt sick for most of the day.  Won't be coming back here again.

text: The food was overpriced for the quality we received. The worst part of the meal was the atmosphere. We had to listen to the owner or manager yell at his staff and micromanage them the entire time. He sat at a table next to us paying his employees. Isn't that what offices are for? During this time we are forced to listen to him air the personal finance business of himself as well as his employees who he obviously had loaned money to. It was a very unpleasant experience, not to mention so very unprofessional. I would never recommend this restaurant to anyone. Remove the manager/owner and this place might have a chance!

Inexpensive, tucked away, dark little getaway from the mainstream.

This is a good bar to go to with friends or if you're hiding from the law. It's not near anything else, and you don't go there to meet people, but it does have quality food and beer for pretty cheap (quite a bit less than most other bars in Dunedin/Palm Harbor.)

categories: Venues & Event Spaces, Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel, Restaurants, Hotels
text:
I stayed here for two nights on a business trip.  My room was cold and the thermostat didn't work.  Having already unpacked all of my belongings, I wasn't too happy when they finally told me I would have to change rooms.  When I expressed my frustration, they promised me vouchers for breakfast.  I was very busy during my stay and didn't have time to complain even more when they failed to deliver on their promise.  
For a supposedly "nice hotel", it was showing signs of wear and the elevators were SLOW.  
I've been in far worse places.  When I return to Philly to see my client next year, I'll probably stay there again because of location.  However, overall, I wasn't very impressed.

text: I arrived at this location at about 11:30 PM and the employee working the drive thru window told me they are only taking credit card transactions. Ended up going to McDonald's next door waiting almost 15 minutes in their drive thru. I find it hard to believe that Taco Bell won't take CASH at 11:30. McDonald's next door happily took my cash and that's why I won't trust this Taco Bell in the future.

text: We drove down to Sewell NJ from our home in Jersey City (almost 2 hours) for an event. Afterwards we wanted to get a bite to eat and found the Barnsboro Inn. The restaurant side had such charm as did our amazing server Shayne M.  The food was amazing!  We had the clams (perfectly shucked), the seared tuna excellent, and finished with a cheese steak and crab cake sandwich. All in all it was a perfect meal as was our conversation with Shayne.  When we come back to south jersey we know exactly where to go and eat!!  Thank you!

name: Denny's
categories: American (Traditional), Breakfast & Brunch, Restaurants, Diners
text: The only saving grace of this visit was the food, a cheeseburger w/ hash browns, egg & bacon on it (perfect dinner/breakfast combo). It was absolutely freezing inside, if I didn't have long sleeves on, there is no way I could've stayed there! Service was painfully slow when there were barely any people in there, I would say about 75% empty. The true icing on the cake was when I went to pay; this masculine woman at the register did not look even look up, didn't say "give me a minute", didn't ask how my meal was, NOTHING. I stood there for 30 seconds before she scanned my receipt in. I had exact change ready. I paid & said "thank you". She literally responded in the most irritated tone, "UH HUUUUH" & nothing else! I was honestly taken back w/ her demeanor & her obvious lack of customer service skills. I'm from NY & expect a little more Southern hospitality than a disgruntled "uh huh". Again, b/c the food was good, that is the only reason I didn't give 1 star.

name: Buffalo Wild Wings
categories: American (Traditional), Sports Bars, Chicken Wings, Nightlife, Restaurants, Bars
text: Well it really takes a lot for me to write a poor review, but this visit was the final straw.   Arrived at the location at noon and sat in the bar.  Waitress was timely and got our drinks and took our order.   We waited and waited and waited  for 35 minutes for a order to come out..  please note after 10 minutes, I started watching the kitchen and very few orders were coming out.  When our order arrived it was wrong..  All the little sticker were correct but the actual food was wrong.  What were the cooks and or expediter thinking/doing?   We had another appointment so we didn't trust they could fix both our orders timely, so we sent the food back and asked for the manager.  The manager came out said she was sorry and that she would take care of our bill..???  For the 2 sodas we had??  She was clueless so we let her know we didn't get to eat and she just looked at us blankly.  Maybe she  should have been all over her kitchen as to their performance as this is not the first time we had the same issues here.  I guess they have earned their 2 star rating.

name: Franks Restaurant
categories: Restaurants, Italian, American (Traditional), Seafood
text:
If I could give this a 0 star review, I absolutely would. We waited to be seated for while, which was fine. Honestly the shortest wait, given everywhere else was over an hour. The wait was short for a reason... the locals know better than to eat there. The food was awful. We paid 60 dollars for food that seemed to be microwaved. 
But this wasn't even the the thing that turned us away... Our waiter was a tall slim man, whose name I can't recall. He was crying out of frustration from the amount of work he had earlier that morning. At first we were understanding and continued to be kind with the intention of tipping large. And then.... he started cussing out loud, very loudly.. at his co workers, and just in general with the intention of all of the customers hearing. He was throwing stuff, punched the bar, yelling and I even heard him at one point make a waitress feel bad for not sharing her tip from her table. He's not quite on purpose. 
He had tables waiting over an hour on food on the outside patio who wound up leaving due to his attitude and lack of service. He had 3 tables including ours at this time. Abigail had the rest and was killing it, she was great. We overheard the table next to us thank her for her great service compared to our waiters. 
We went to the manager and she acted like it was not a big deal. She just apologized and said "he has only been here for 3 days and he's overwhelmed "...
I get being overwhelmed, but the attitude he had and his actions were unacceptable. 
The poor younger guy waiting tables told my spouse "I have to deal with this everyday". 
I feel so bad for his co workers. 
I will never eat at this place again and I suggest you don't either unless you like garbage food, poor management and bad attitudes.
As far as covid guidelines go, they have none. No one wore a mask, not even employees. Our waiter was wiping his running nose with the back of his hand and brought us our food with those same disgusting hands. 
Our table was not clean when we were sat down. 
The experience was just terrible all together. 
Go somewhere else, it's worth the wait. 

But if you choose to go anyway, ask for Abigail and to be as far away as possible from that man we had.

name: Panache Woodfire Grill
categories: Desserts, American (Traditional), Restaurants, Food, Sandwiches, Pizza
text: Being in the service industry for 7 years, I understand how hard it can be to work in a restaurant, especially during these times; However, this is easily the worst experience I have ever had at a restaurant. To start, my boyfriend and I had a 6:30 reservation and were told by the hosts (who did not properly wear their masks) we'd have to wait 20 minutes until being seated. Once seated, we were sat three feet away from the band, which was extremely loud and unenjoyable, so we had asked if we could move and we waited another 20 minutes for another table. While waiting, hostesses were talking about us complaining that we wanted to move when our reservation was for the dining room, not outside directly next to the band. Finally, we sat 40 minutes past our scheduled reservation and had the pleasure of being sat with our server, Brian. Brian failed to 1) pick up the check on the table from the previous people 2) deliver my coke before my appetizers 3) stick his hand in my drink and touch my straw and 4) forgot to ring in both of our entrees in which we sat and waited 90 minutes for. For the record, my boyfriends cheese steak was burnt and my salad had approximately four leafs of lettuce on it. On top of that, we barely got any refills and he was extremely hard to locate, not when he ran the card though of course. To end this fabulous evening panache, Brian had dropped the card on the floor prior to checking us out. I'm not one to usually complain, but our experience here was almost laughable. I won't be returning and I won't recommending this place to anyone.

name: Smoky Mountain Pizzeria Grill
categories: Pizza, Italian, Burgers, Restaurants
text:
UPDATE 6/2:  What a difference a few weeks make!  After my original review I heard from Tom, the owner, a few days later.   He informed me of some shift adjustments and in house training and asked that we try again with the provided gift card.  We did tonight and are glad we did.  The food looks great and it arrived in 25 minutes when they gave an estimate of 45 to an hour.  The star rating will definitely go up in the future if this continues.  Tasty food!


What in the world is going on with the Park Center location?  This evening was our third time ordering delivery from them in the past few months and it will be the last.  We placed our order at 4pm, were told it could be up to an hour and we were fine with that.  The turkey club is worth waiting for when done right. 

Well, it's now 6pm and our driver just arrived.  So a 2 hour wait instead of 1.  Okay, I'm upset but not overly so.  Then I see our food.  What a joke.  Compare my two turkey clubs to the picture on the menu.  Where is the lettuce, onion,  tomato and sauce?  Oh, and the pasta, cold.

Naturally we called to complain.  The manager on duty, Nicole, said she can send replacement sandwiches out.  Not really an option in my opinion since based on delivery times I'd be eating at 8.  She then said she would send a gift card for the cost of two turkey clubs.  Neat, so in the future I can go through this again.  

Bottom line,  if the wait is long, make it worth waiting for.  Don't deliver a sandwich missing half its components.   Don't put pasta in a container an hour and a half before delivering it.  Seems like common sense to me.

Maybe I wouldn't be so upset but as I mentioned in the beginning,  this is the third time recently and every delivery has had mistakes.  The wrong pasta the first time.   And a wedge salad that was just lettuce and bacon, no dressing,  onions,  etc the second time. Just a wilted wedge of lettuce and a few bits of bacon.  It made me wish I had a rabbit to feed it to.  

Oh well, we're done.  Ownership really needs to take a close look at this location, it's falling apart.  Anyone want the gift card, if and when I receive it?  I won't be using it.

name: Holiday Inn New Orleans-Downtown Superdome
categories: Hotels & Travel, Party & Event Planning, Event Planning & Services, American (Traditional), Resorts, Hotels, Restaurants, Venues & Event Spaces
text:
My girl friends and I really couldn't have asked for a better hotel during our visit to New Orleans. The staff was friendly and was able to check us into our 16th-floor room early. The view we had was awesome - we could see the Superdome! The balcony was a nice thing to have in a relatively inexpensive city hotel. The room was spacious and clean. We loved that there was an extra sink available. Wi-Fi is free, which we sincerely appreciated. 

The hotel's lobby and common areas are modern without being tacky. My friends and I especially enjoyed the lobby and bar. The hotel staff was all really friendly and quick to answer the few questions we had. Checking in and out was easy and painless! I'd definitely recommend this hotel to anyone looking to visit the city on a budget.

name: Mimi's Cafe
categories: Cajun/Creole, Restaurants, Coffee & Tea, American (Traditional), French, Food, Breakfast & Brunch
text: My daughter and her boyfriend to me to dinner this evening.  After we were seated the waiter came over and took the drink and appetizer order.  When he came back to get the food order a third drink was ordered.  Had to ask for 3 set of silverware and ask for the 3rd drink a second time after the meal came.  Our waiter seemed lost and confused the whole time we were there.  We had Spinach dip and chips, Turkey w/Brie, Quiche Loraine and soup.  Mine also came with a muffin that I asked to have it packaged to go.  At the end of our meal asked for to go containers, had to ask a second time for the muffin.  This is one of the reasons I usually don't go in the evenings.  The service is questionable.  The food on the other hand was wonderful.  tomato basil soup and French onion soup were great.  The quiche Loraine had a wonderful crust and was light and filling.  It had been a long time since I have eaten here.  I may go back for breakfast, probably not for dinner.

name: Shake Shack
categories: Restaurants, Burgers
text:
Any elementary schools looking for field trip opportunities to explore democracy in action: look no further!  Coming from a place of relative wealth and privilege (at least in the global sense), I arrogantly assumed that an order consisting of nothing but a large Diet Coke would be fulfilled while I waited at the counter.  Boy, did I ever get an egalitarian comeuppance.
Instead of the soft drink, I was served a blinking, buzzing Pager of Justice.  The message was clear: no amount of wealth or power receives preferential treatment at the Shake Shack!  Nay!  I was to join my party at a table to await the convulsions of my assigned pager like everyone - regardless of the size or value of their orders.  
I only wish that instead of the counter attendant bellowing my name with the sweet staccato of equality, an eagle in stars & stripes silken boxer shorts dove from the rafters with my Diet Coke clutched in it's talons.  But that would be an overly elaborate process to serve a soda.

name: Olive Garden Italian Restaurant
categories: Salad, Nightlife, Bars, Soup, Italian, Wine Bars, Restaurants
text:
Olive Garden is a great chain restaurant, I go here for simple basic Italian food, with decent prices. I was not pleased with this location. I've now been in Arizona for a year and this was my first visit. Craving a little of the soup, and salad, my husband and I decided to pop in for a Wednesday lunch. I can honestly say, I didn't care for anything from the service to the food quality here today. 
I give 2 stars because 1. The place was clean, and updated decor made it feel nicer than other Olive Gardens! And 2.its Olive Garden and the prices were what was expected. 
The bad-well, to start our Order was taken by our server, Tyler, who was probably not best suited for front of the house work. He wasn't friendly, or happy to be there, and I heard an adjacent table say "ouch, he doesn't like his job!" And I agree. No smile no nothing. My husband ordered spaghetti, I had soup and salad, and we shared the breadsticks.   Soup and salad came out quick-breadsticks were stale as if they had been sitting for while. Meanwhile, we began eating, all salad and soup gone-hubbys spaghetti was not out yet. We waited at the table with no food-and no server in sight. Long long long wait, we finally see Tyler and ask for refills on all and spaghetti. A little annoyed sigh, and he went and got all. 
We didn't see Tyler again until he was flagged down by another table. Unfortunately this was not the usual Olive Garden experience I've come to know, and we won't return to this location

name: P J Whelihan's Pub & Restaurant - Blue Bell
categories: Nightlife, Restaurants, Burgers, American (New), American (Traditional), Chicken Wings, Bars, Sports Bars, Gastropubs
text:
summary ... good beer selection, okay food, can get crazy busy at happy hour

The one major draw for PJ Wheilans is that they have a great beer selection.  It's almost as good as Blue Dog Pub's beer selection, but still nowhere near something like Monk's Caf (in Center City) or Craft Ale House (in Limerick).  It's good enough though that when a happy hour (or trivia or something else) is setup here, I'm usually up for going (unlike Bones Grille).  The food is okay, nothing special, just the standard pub fare.  I haven't had any complaints about it, but I also can't think of any compliments after several visits.

The service is not bad, not the most attentive, but again, no major complaints.  My one major complaint about PJW is that it can get insanely busy for some happy hour periods (especially on Fridays).  Like busy enough that it becomes difficult to hear your group.

Basically, this place is a nice middle of the road option that should meet everyone's expectations.  Nothing amazing, but consistently not bad.

text: Hmmmm, so the reason why I went to this place is the smell.. Outside you'll smell those burnt meat.. Yummmm. It's a great place to hangout and relax.. Very cheap eats. I got the lamb, chicken, beef, squid, and fishballs.. all were great, except for the squid, has rubbery texture, and the fishballs were chewy.. and cold on the inside.. The beef and lamb were my favorite.. If I come back it's for the beef and lamb only

name: IKEA
categories: Kitchen & Bath, Shopping, Restaurants, Furniture Stores, Nurseries & Gardening, Home Decor, Appliances, Home & Garden
text:
Damn IKEA! My apartment looks like a reality tv show set.

Hint: Remember to have a plate of meatballs along the way.

Hint: Great for small spaces and for people who can't commit to any furniture for long periods because they move around a lot or have commitment issues.

Beware: some cheap items are just that, cheap! Just return them if you're unhappy. They've never hassled me on a return. Eg: I bought a Gilbert chair, screwed in the screws for the metal legs with my manly man arms (not), and the screws went through the wood seat and poked you when you sat down. Then again, maybe u like to get poked?

Tip: have enough in your checking account before you go and use your debit card - you get a coupon worth 3% of your current purchase for your next purchase. Don't lose it! If you don't plan on coming back, save a small item from your purchase. Make your purchase, get your coupon, then use the coupon for the small item.

name: Rosalita's Cantina
categories: Restaurants, Mexican, Bars, Tex-Mex, Cocktail Bars, Nightlife
text: Besides the impressive patio and sleek dcor, Rosalita's is basic. The food isn't anything spectacular and it's always too crowded. And I really don't know why since there are much better options for Mexican in the area. I only go to Rosalita's because some of my friends truly do like it and I must admit, it has a decent happy hour. Speaking of happy hour, I would like to add something that annoyed me when I was there last night. It's not a huge deal-it's just the principle of the thing. So I was there with friends for drinks and wells are $3 during HH. I ordered a cranberry vodka and when I got the bill it was $3 for the well and an additional $.50 for the cranberry juice. I just thought it was petty of Rosalita's. Like do you really need to charge that extra $.50? I understand that premium mixers are typically more, but cranberry juice? That seems pretty ordinary for a well drink and it rubbed me the wrong way. Probably since I already don't care for the place that much anyway. If it were up to me, I would never go back. Not because of the $.50 thing but because the place lacks flavor and the menu is boring. Instead go to Chavas in Soulard or Casa Juarez, which was once Chihuahuas.

categories: Nightlife, Restaurants, Seafood, American (New), Bars, Sports Bars, American (Traditional)
text: Been here more than a few times, atmosphere is nice, place & bathroom always clean. But I really think they should stick to bar foods, their dinners are really horrible. After the second time of not eating hardly anything off my plate I won't be getting a dinner from here again. The first time it was the ribs, tasted like hotdogs, and a over cooked potatoes. The second time it was their "special" blue cheese pork chops, the plate was the most pathetic thing I've ever seen, 3 tiny pork chops, not too bad but I think they forgot to cook the one, a potato I wouldn't give to the dogs and mushy, yet hard corn. After asking for another potato I received another just as bad. I ended up sharing my husbands shrimp platter and left mine on the table. Their zingers and other bar foods are good however.

name: La Parrilla Suiza
categories: Mexican, Restaurants
text:
I've been to this place since I was a teen (oh geez, a good 20 years!) grew into an adult coming here, brought my own children here, this place was so dear to my heart, it was the venue for my wedding rehearsal dinner! Then I moved away to north Florida where the best Mexican food you're gonna get is at home and you get excited about a Chipotle opening up! 

After four years of being away, I finally came back to Tucson! First on the list- La Parilla, of course! I was so excited to go back. We had a party of 13, nothing too crazy, but it took them over 30 minutes to sit us on a slow Tuesday night around 7:30. Then our server seemed so overwhelmed! He took our drink orders (nervously) and went away for about 20 minutes. This place hosted more than 60 of us before! What's going on? My mom saw a server she has known for years and waived her down. She asked about our drinks and just then the guy comes to give us our drinks. I don't know where he was this whole time, but the ice in my margarita was so melted it was almost gone and made the drink taste watery. He brought the kids cup without a lid! The waiter clearly had issues, he disappeared again for a good 20 minutes without even taking our food order. So my moms waitress friend comes by again and ends up taking up our table! What in the world is going on here? Anyway, she was much nicer and attentive. Service was A+ after she took over, she brought out a fresh margarita, a lid for the kids cup, but then......

Our food arrived! My long awaited (4 years) delicious, life long favorite food! And my heart broke. It was so sadly bad! Everything has changed! The fajitas were burned! The chicken melt was on a soggy tortilla, the beans were bland, and worst of all, the rice was completely different!!!! They had this delicious, lightly seasoned yellow rice for as long as I've known of this place and all the sudden it's mushy orange rice? Not even good for Spanish rice! I think Taco Bell has better Spanish rice and I am NOT kidding. It was mush. The yellow rice was their signature to me! No one else had it! How disappointing. 

The only good thing was the chips and salsa. I am so sad about this place. We have lost a family tradition.

text:
For those of you that have never tried Fazoli's, its fast Italian food, the quality isn't as good as it used to be, however it a nice change of pace from the traditional fast food routine. Even better if you are in the mood for a quick Italian style dinner and are limited on time. No the food will not win any awards or be something you praise to anyone, its just fairly cheap, fast Italian food.

As far as this location goes, its about average. My most recent visit they seemed to mess up my order after reading it back correct. No big deal, however I think that they can focus a little bit on customer service.

categories: Restaurants, Hotels & Travel, Arts & Entertainment, Casinos, Hotels, Event Planning & Services
text: A terrific breakfast for $4.99? That's right. My family and I were hungry (including 5 kids) and the sign made us circle back to give it a try. Boy are we glad that we did! The $4.99 steak and eggs breakfast was a real value. The steak was quite tasty and cooked as ordered, accompanied by two eggs, hashbrowns and toast. There were at least half a dozen other breakfast and lunch specials for $4.99 and dinner specials starting at $5.99. We would definitely go back again.

name: Gullifty's Restaurant
categories: Italian, Pizza, Restaurants, American (Traditional), Bars, Nightlife, American (New)
text: I have never been treated so poorly. I walked in at 620 pm. Was greeted by the two girls at the door. Before i had a chance to say anything, what appeared to be the owner came up to the hostess desk and started spewing orders about combining tables for large parties. He then looked at me and said do you need something? My reply was yes I'd like to sit at the bar. He looked down and said there's not a lot of room but you might be able to sit at a hightop. Then went back  to work on seating the large parties. I was a party of one, and there was a single table available. But I never had the opportunity to ask for it. Do not ever come here. They should be ashamed of themselves. I realize it was a Saturday night, but because I was a party of one I felt ignored. Shame on you.

name: Del Frisco's Grille
categories: Steakhouses, Nightlife, American (New), Sandwiches, Bars, Restaurants, Fast Food, Cocktail Bars
text:
Cons- 
Parking in this area is always a pain but doable. Valet is an option though. 
Prices seemed a bit high for many of the items on the menu. 
My chicken cesar salad was good but bland.

More importantly the PROS-
Wonderful serves. Informative, helpful, attentive and the list goes on & a manager came by the table to check on our meal.  
White sangria served with homemade popsicle!!!  So yummy I had to have two.  
Beautiful place & really cool patio area. 
My friend had to special order the flatbread due to allergies and they accommodated without a problem and her flatbread was delicious. 

This was my first visit. My friend was able to name many items off the menu that her family had tried and enjoyed including the burger, pork chop, meatloaf & sides. 

A little pricey but then again it's a cool atmosphere, great serves & pretty great food.

This restaurant should be closed down!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

name: Pat's King of Steaks
categories: Italian, American (Traditional), Sandwiches, Fast Food, Restaurants, Local Flavor, Cheesesteaks
text: I need to go back here and try a few more to be able to give them more than 3 stars,  but for the culinary experience, historical significance and cheese steak sandwiches we had, 3 stars for now.  Just to note: the line and way you order is important so be ready for this.  The great debate over who has the best Philly Cheese Steak sandwich, Geno's or Pat's, is not over.  Check out my review of Geno's because we tried them both at the same time.  Fear None, Love All, and Eat Well.

name: Joe Italiano's Maplewood
categories: Restaurants, Italian, Soup, Salad
text:
40 minute wait for a table. 60 minute wait for dinner. 
- bread - fine
- house salad - pretty basic, iceberg lettuce
- fresh pasta - not at all distinguishable from shop-rite box pasta 
- garlic and olive oil - bitter garlic with low quality oil
- espresso - watery

Waiter didn't comment on the fact that I didn't take more than three bites of my dinner.

Lovely building but I would never eat there again 

Ps - three of their six veggies are potatoes and the fourth is coleslaw - probably should have know what I was walking into right then

name: Golden Flower Vietnamese
categories: Restaurants, Desserts, Vietnamese, Bars, Chinese, Food, Soup, Nightlife
text:
I recently rediscovered Golden Flower after a moving back to this side of town and I could not be more thrilled! I can't believe the years I wasted going to other Pho places when this one is so amazing! 

First of all, you absolutely need to have the Pot Stickers. They are seriously amazing! The dough is SO unbelievably fresh and the sauce is to die for. 

In terms of entrees, we've ordered from both the Vietnamese and the Chinese menu and never been disappointed. I love the BBQ pork on the Vietnamese menu either as a noodle dish or as an entree with rice. The Pho soup is also delicious. The lemon chicken is ridiculous. Awesome flavors.

This place is open late and is a great place to get takeout if you need something for a weeknight. If you dine in, the food comes out pretty quick and the place is almost always packed for dinner. Just call your order in if you are picking up, it can sometimes be a bit of a wait.

name: Good Times Saloon
categories: Nightlife, Sports Bars, Beer Bar, Bars, Restaurants, American (Traditional)
text:
It's Burger week! We were super excited about stop number 1 for the hot and spicy burger here at Good Times Saloon in Dupo. Upon entering we noticed the facility is split into two sections, a bar and a restaurant. We moseyed on over to the restaurabring side and took a seat. We waited about 10 minutes before someone came to take our order (Keep in mind we were the only couple of the establishment). We ordered the six dollar burger, an order of onion rings, and an order of toasted raviolis. After about 20 minutes of waiting the server came back to let us know that they forgot to put the order in and we weren't terribly concerned about it until the food arrived. The description of this burger is supposed to be a thick patty, battered and deep-fried jalapenos, a runny egg, and a Chipotle aioli with melted pepper jack cheese. What we got was a very thin frozen patty, a perfectly cooked egg, jalapenos fresh out of the jar and no other sauces or condiments on a store-bought bun. As you can tell from the photo, this is not the same animal as what's advertised for this establishment. After bringing it up to the server, she brought us a small thing of battered and fried jalapenos( which were delicious), still no aioli and still an inedible Burger. 

The highlight of this sandwich was the perfectly cooked egg, which is pretty impressive this day in age. Outside of that, we did not eat more than 2 bites of this sandwich and it was highly disappointing. On a positive note, the onion rings and toasted ravioli (straight from the hill) were exceptional. The service was bad, yet friendly. Our Hope of finding a diamond in the rough fell short and unfortunately, we will not be back.

name: Lu Lu Seafood & Dim Sum
categories: Dim Sum, Restaurants, Noodles, Chinese, Seafood
text:
You need strategy for Dim Sum.

I went there with my friend for lunch around 1:00 pm on Saturday and ordered Dim Sum. They have several food wagons for dumplings, meet, vegetables, desserts, and so on, and you can take food on plates from each wagon that you like. Therefore, you cannot eat varieties of food if you get too much food from the first wagon. Please be careful !! :D

Unfortunately, we went there around 1:00 pm, there are less kinds of food rest than usual, and food was getting a little cold. I think that you had better go there earlier.

The cost depends on sizes of plates, and the sizes are obscure and not clear, so I recommend you to confirm which size the plate is before you take food from wagons.

I enjoyed Dim Sum. I would like to go to a restaurant in a China town to eat Dim Sum again!!

name: Sea Sea Riders Restaurant
categories: Nightlife, Restaurants, Bars, Seafood
text:
My fiance and I decided to stop in to grab an early dinner and get out of the heat after walking around the Dunedin craft festival. The waitress didn't have a clue what the happy hour specials were; she had to go to the bar to ask! I ordered the Mahi Mahi, which I regretted not sending back. It was 2 small pieces of previously frozen fish...very dry and bland. The fried green tomatoes did not taste good and the side of roast beet remoulade was so small, I don't even know why they bothered to put it on the plate. And for this dish we paid $17.70!!
My fiance got the mussels which also were dry.
However, the key lime pie martini and flourless chocolate torte were absolutely delicious. We may return to this establishment for drinks or dessert only, but never again would we order entrees.

name: Domino's Pizza
categories: Restaurants, Pizza, Chicken Wings, Sandwiches
text:
Domino's Pizza isn't gourmet, but it's quick, inexpensive (if you're picking it up), and pretty tasty.  I recommend either using the app to order because you will always have coupons at your finger tips or ordering the $5 medium pizzas, which you have to order at least 3 of.

This particular location is pretty convenient for the Metairie/Lakeview area.  It's right off Old Hammond Highway, and it's located on a corner, so you can zip into the parking lot, grab your pizza, and be on your way in no time at all.  The staff also seem pretty friendly and courteous.  

Overall, a solid "fast food" pizza option.

text: Rated a 2 for location and atmosphere,  if not for that it would be 1. We had reservations & we asked the hostess seating us for a table by the windows (there was several available). She informed us they were for  reservations. When we informed her we had reservations she acted very annoyed and had to check on it. She came back & seated is @ table by the window.  Well, it was a good thing. We could watch the street action while we waited endlessly for our drinks & food. Our server was pleasant, not her fault for how ridiculously slow the delivery of drinks & food arrived. The food was cold because the kitchen was on a different floor so they brought it up on a very busy elevator filled with patrons & food servers. Not the best arrangement.

name: Fountain Grill - Safety Harbor Resort and Spa
categories: Mediterranean, Restaurants
text:
I live a few minutes from the Safety Harbor Spa. It is a beautiful location so we decide to support a local business for Thanksgiving. We are a family of two so we always eat out for holiday meals. I booked the reservation weeks before the holiday and arrived 10
minutes before our reservation. The meal itself was a prix fixed meal at $35 per person. Not a huge price but expensive enough to expect decent service. As soon
as we checked in, we were told there was not a 2 person table available so they could set us at the end of large families table that had two open chairs. WHAT???? I don't want to have dinner with my extended family much less a strange family. They didn't look thrilled either. When I refused that arrangement, they offered to pull the small table away from the larger party. Basically, the table is now two feet from the other party and half way into the check in area. The only other option offered was to have dinner in the lounge which was full and extremely loud due to live music. We finally got the manager involved and he found a table outside on the patio and set up a heater to keep off the chill. We order our food. The soup ( lobster bisque) tasted fantastic unfortunately neither of us got even a pea sized piece of lobster. I am willing to forget this because it is hotel dinner not 5 star. Once the food comes, the waitress who hasn't been back since dropping off the soups was smart enough to bring drink
Refills. We got one turkey and one salmon. The turkey was okay some pieces were rubbery but it had a tasty gravy. The mashed potatoes were dried out but with some added butter they were decent. The salmon was way too salty and mediocre at best. 
I am telling myself at this point nothing is perfect but for an $85 meal for two I am not real happy. Then disaster strikes!!! I look down and see something on the side of my glass. On further inspection, I realize it is dried food stuck to the inside of my glass. And it has friends!!! A smear of food dried all the way down the glass and another clump around the bottom the size of a Lima bean. Not a little speck but a significant piece of food stuck on the inside of my glass. After waiting 5 minutes to get the waitress back over, she tries to tell me it is a lemon seed. When I put the glass in front of her face, she said "eww that is gross" "sorry about that, do want another drink".  Yes, oh course I want another drink. I am trying not to think about how the food got in the glass so I don't throw up the mediocre dinner I am paying $85. She did bring another drink in a clean glass. No further apology or acknowledgment of the incident. I expected at least an apology from the manager. We had to
Put in our dessert order three times because the waiter forgot the order and we asked for coffee. It was good coffee but the carafe was filthy on the outside. Coffee stains and crud in the cracks on the outside of the carafe. Even greasy spoon dinners wipe down to carafes before serving you coffee. Overall, it was more like truck stop  service than elegant hotel service. The food was just mediocre. I wouldn't come back at $40 per person. It is a shame because the setting is beautiful.

name: Vincentown Diner
categories: Diners, American (New), Restaurants, American (Traditional), Sandwiches
text:
Recently I decided to try out the Vincentown Diner again. I know it has under gone some changes over the past few years and had a reputation in the area for being pricey. My friend and I were seated quickly and the male waiter was impressively attentive. A few years back I had a waitress here who was more interested in flirting with a customer than tending her tables. From the signs on the highway one gets the idea that the new owner must be trying something new (Organic eggs, certified Angus beef). The menu seemed even more progressive (No trans fats, locally grown produce, locally produced wines, and even locally raised pasture fed beef.)
  I went for the pasture fed burger with the asiago cheese and bacon on top with the hand cut steak fries on the side. My friend went for the open faced turkey sandwich with homemade cranberry sauce. Again the service was exceptional. The food arrived hot with restaurant presentation and not just lumped on the plate. One might think we were at some fancy place and not just the corner diner. What a difference! I could actually taste the burger. It was charred just enough on the outside and pink and dripping with flavor inside.
  I'll have to come back again and try some of these other special locally grown dishes. My only complaint was the coffee wasn't drinkable. I'll have to check back to see if this is normal for this local land mark. Comparing prices to some other diners Vincentown is a little more money. But if you have eaten at Mastoris lately these prices compare favorably and the food tastes so much better.

name: Hamilton's Grill Room
categories: Event Planning & Services, Steakhouses, Greek, American (New), Seafood, Mediterranean, Caterers, Restaurants
text:
Visiting a friend in nearby New Town for the weekend, we planned a girls' night out which included dinner at Hamilton's.  Two of three in our party had dined here before, but I was a first timer... and after our meal, I can safely say that none of us will be rushing back.

Sure, the restaurant offers a fun atmosphere with plenty of seating both inside and out; it has a scenic view of the Delaware Canal; and it's located in the fun area of Lambertville.  It's BYOB and has a diverse selection of menu items from veggies, salads, soups, oysters, steaks, seafood and more.  

Unfortunately, the service we experienced was horrendous.  We arrived promptly for our 7:30 reservation and were seated right away, but weren't greeted by a server for a good ten minutes.  Once we were greeted, it took another 30+ minutes to place our food order, and then we waited more than an hour and fifteen minutes before our entrees arrived.

That being said, we did have oysters (a couple of different kinds) that were awesome.  We attempted to order a salad but were told they were out of the salad we wanted....  bummer.  We also shared a side of cauliflower pure, a side of asparagus, and the scallop entree.  All were OK - nothing to write home about.

We would have liked to wash dinner down with water in addition to our wine, but we had to ask several times before getting that... 

The manager was more apologetic to us than our waiter was, and the table next to us made a point to lean over to share their disappointment with the service as well.

I recommend that if you do head to Hamilton's, to do so on a weeknight... unless you don't mind a very long and leisurely meal.

name: Bonefish Grill
categories: Seafood, American (New), Cocktail Bars, Restaurants, Nightlife, Bars
text: This is my second visit to a Bonefish Grill and my first at this location.  First of all, the service was excellent, our waiter was friendly, engaging and made great suggestions.  I had the special broiled salmon.  It was cooked perfectly as I asked for it to be medium rare.  My friend had the special stuffed crab and I noticed there was not a morsel of that entire crab left on her plate.  The strawberry shortcake dessert included a dish full of fresh strawberries and fresh whipped cream.  The pastry was just the right amount.  I really don't understand the comments about the portions being too small.  It's time we stop expecting to receive more food that we could possibly eat and leave a good portion of it on the plate.  The amounts were just right!  P.S.  Their Martini's are great!

name: Brick House Tavern + Tap
categories: Restaurants, Food, Nightlife, Pizza, Sports Bars, Sandwiches, Bars, American (Traditional), American (New), Burgers
text:
I was here on a Saturday afternoon while college football was on.  The restaurant was not busy but the service was incredibly slow.  The lone bartender struggled to get our table of 8 drinks in under 20 minutes and let my beer sit out and get warm for 10 of those minutes.  My cheesesteak was way over salted and several people got soggy lettuce in their salad.  Somebody used the term "rubbery chicken" when asked how their chicken sandwich was.  I'd recommend choosing any other local establishment before venturing here.

I literally downloaded Yelp at the table just to write this review.  Interior here is pretty cool, but that's the only positive takeaway.

name: The Old No 77 Hotel and Chandlery
categories: Hotels, Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel, Restaurants
text:
So, we pull into New Orleans for the night and have chosen Old No 77 to stay in as they accept pets. To be honest I was not expecting much but was pleasantly surprised at this little gem. The parking and valet were very nice. The front desk loved our dog and set us up in our room. We take the elevator to the second floor and navigate the maze and find that room and walk in. I am telling you it was all good.  The brick walls and the decor all went together and we were instantly at ease and felt at home, more importantly the dog was loving all the attention she got from the staff and was not freaking out on this first road trip.

We head out to the town and are not able to get 20 feet without someone stopping to pet the dog and ask a ton of questions. Love New Orleans!!!

And yes we felt very safe walking everywhere. Finding grass for the dog was challenging but there is a park behind the hotel within walking distance that worked out great. Again we had no issues at night or any time of the day.

Anyway, we wake up the next morning to hit the road and go downstairs to pack up thinking we will grab something to eat on the way but then notice the breakfast spread on the way out. To pass that bad boy up would be a horrible mistake. So we alter the plan and take a table with the dog. I swear we get one of everything, it all looked great and the again the staff is awesome. 

So yes, if your looking for a great place to stay that has a great location that is walking distance to all the fun then check this place out. If your looking for a great friendly place that will love your pet and not give you any crap like other places, then this is the place, again they could not have been nicer.

text:
I used to like this place, but my last visit was quite bad, and the 2 previous visits were disappointing. At the last visit I ordered an enchilada combo with one pork and one cheese. Neither had sauces on them; the pork should have had a green sauce but was dry, and the cheese was just a half-melted piece of cheese wrapped in a tortilla. Also, the beans were just ordinary baked beans, neither refried nor black beans.

Finally, the lunch menu had been largely eliminated, so I paid dinner prices for a bad lunch.

name: Taziki's Mediterranean Cafe - Hendersonville
categories: Vegetarian, Mediterranean, Restaurants, Gluten-Free
text: I got the shrimp plate with basmati rice. The shrimp was cooked to perfection - tender, juicy, and well seasoned. The Greek salad that came with it was fresh and crispy. The Greek dressing is really tasty too - right amount of acidity and sweetness. I ordered a side of tzatziki sauce and for me that was not good. It tasted too milky (like the aftertaste of cowmilk) but maybe that's how it's supposed to be? Other tzatziki sauces I've had were not like that but I suppose it all depends on your preference. Got a side of sweet tea as well; it was right amount of sweetness and no weird after taste. Highly recommend this place!

name: LongHorn Steakhouse
categories: Restaurants, Steakhouses, Barbeque, American (Traditional)
text:
Ate here for my grandmother's birthday. Looked like a long wait but were seated within 10 minutes. The bar wasn't very busy during our wait but never got our beef before we were called for our table. We ordered ya the table instead. The beer is cold!! The food came out pretty fast. 
My grandmother is very picky. She ordered the filet and said it was delicious. She said it was cooked as she ordered and liked the hot baked potato. I had the wedge salad. However, it's not a wedge. It's several pieces of romaine lettuce. It had too much blue cheese but it was still good. My husband got chopped steak with rosemary bolognese and said it was excellent. The kids split a full rack of ribs and ate every single one of them.
Service was attentive and quick. The atmosphere is nice. Music isn't too loud. Decor is tasteful. 
We finished it off with a free Birthday Sundae! Great night!

name: Shagun Palace
categories: Indian, Vegetarian, Buffets, Restaurants, Event Planning & Services, Caterers, Halal
text:
This is the first time (and last) my mom and I have gone to this buffet/restaurant. First thing, we get there, we are seated, and served glasses of water.  Cool! It's a buffet, so basically the water is your cue to help yourself.  I will admit that, being a vegetarian, and mom is on and off, I was pleased to see that they had a good variety of veg/non veg food.

I first set down a few small bowls of chutneys at our table to have with our meal.  Not even 10 minutes later, we just get done making our plates of food, and find that not only has the staff removed our entire place setting, but there is another group sitting there! Mind you, the restaurant still had several available seats.  So naturally, we made somewhat of a (DF?) fuss.  The staff basically stood staring at us dumbfound until we just sat at another table.  The remainder of the time was just awkward; probably contributing to us not enjoying our food. I actually wanted to leave at that point but mom wanted to stay.

When I rank Indian food, I'm basically comparing it to that of my family's.   The pani puri was a delight to see since my regular Indian buffet never has them.  The garlic naan bread and dal were pretty good, and so was the gulab jamun.  But the rice was severely under-cooked and crunchy. How disappointing not being able to have basmati rice at an Indian restaurant! According to mom, it seems that they may have confused sugar for salt in another one of their rice dishes, and the chicken tandoori was RAW and slimy. And of course not one more word from the staff.  I didn't even want to drink the replacement waters they had given us. We just ate as quickly as we could paid and left.

Will never go back.  I'm sticking to my known and trusted Aman's, pani puri or no.

name: El Limon - Bryn Mawr
categories: Mexican, Restaurants
text:
I've ordered the Cubano tortas here a couple of times and let me just tell you its massive. Like the burger can barely contain all the ingredients within it! It's delicious though, the runny egg goes great with the pork and guac in this sandwich and the jalepenos add some nice kick which comes through really well! One con would be that it is definitely salty which could put some folks slightly off...

The chips are alright, and of the 2 salsas its the green one I prefer here! Nice and spicy!

Flan is one of my favourite desserts, and El Limon has a good flan. It's on the firmer side but tastes well balanced!

I'll give the tacos a shot here soon because...duh? But overall a reasonable option in the area!

name: Ybor City Tap House
categories: Beer Gardens, Mexican, Restaurants, American (New), Beer Bar, Sports Bars, Gastropubs, Nightlife, Bars
text:
First, let me say that I rarely rate anything highly in Ybor. I genuinely get annoyed at the scene down there past 8pm. 

That being said, this tap house has decent food, and specious outdoor seating. There was a HUGE assortment of drinks and you're sure to find something that you like. 

I had the Berry Jam Cider (a recommendation from my waitress) and it was REALLY good. 

The waitstaff took a while to notice I had sat down, but I was waiting for someone and specifically took a seat tucked away, so totally not their fault! Once they noticed me they were incredibly attentive and on top of everything. 

I had the fish and chips which were supposed to come with waffle fries but came with potato chips. Apparently they were out of Waffle fries, no big! But the option for regular fries would have been nice. (I don't really eat chips) 

All together not a bad trip until drunk dudes started randomly sitting down at my table and trying to butt into the conversation that my friend and I were having!

name: Sushi Kingdom
categories: Japanese, Restaurants, Sushi Bars
text:
Terrible terrible service. We got there at 8:30 PM and it was well before 9:30pm (closes at 10pm) and they were already rushing around trying to clean up everything and ignoring the other people like us who were still eating. You don't need THREE people bussing one table. AND the one thing that completely irks me so bad at a restaurant is when you DON'T REFILL MY DRINK. I should not have to wait and wait and wait and choke on my food wondering why the waitresses are all walking by ignoring the fact that my glass is empty because I know you CLEARLY SEE that my glass is empty. You should be bringing us refills automatically or at the very least asking if we even want a refill. If you don't then I won't tip you and fair enough to say I left no tip and will be not be eating here again.

 The only redeeming quality about this place is that their appetizers are good and the sushi is decent for the area.

name: Crooked Tree Coffeehouse
categories: Coffee & Tea, Restaurants, Food
text: Went here with my daughter. Have been here many times in the past. However, it has been at least 8 months since my last visit. Placed our order and 15 min later my daughter received her meal but not my soup. We wait 10 more minutes. Soup still had not arrived so I went to ask for my money back because we had other engagements. Some guy who I had not seen before gave me a very irritated look and handed me back four dollars. No apology, no we will get it right out next time, nothing. I take the money and leave. Upon looking at my receipt in the car, I see the soup cost over $4.50 plus tax. This business no longer cares about their customers or how they treat anyone. That is fine. A reason to never go back.
